title: ms. jessie's cake decorating icing
directions: Mix 1 box of powdered sugar and add second box as needed with Crisco, water and flavoring. This can last safely 2 weeks refrigerated.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In a small bowl, mash avocado until smooth. Stir in yogurt, picante sauce, onion, salt and hot pepper sauce (optional). Cover and refrigerate until serving. Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: 2 servings (3/4 cup).

title: up the holler briarhopper sauce
directions: In large pot, mix ingredients together in the listed order. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for four hours.
Serve hot over your favorite boiled pasta.

title: bambinos
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread rounds with ketchup; top with pepperoni slices.
Sprinkle cheese and oregano over pepperoni. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until cheese is melted, 3 to 4 minutes at 400°.
Yield:
4 dozen canapes.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine; mix well.
Add flour, mixing well.
Chill.
Divide dough into quarters and each quarter into 12 balls.
Press each ball into miniature muffin pan.
Cover bottom and sides well.

title: no flour cookies
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients; mix well.
Make into small balls. Place on an oiled cookie sheet.
Press each ball with a fork that has been dipped in cold water.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut clusters(sue b. king wanjura)
directions: In double boiler, melt morsels and stir in Spanish peanuts. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: chicken salad
directions: Use boneless and skinless chicken breast boiled.
If use whole chicken breast, after cooked skin and debone.
Cut in chunks.
Mix all ingredients; except eggs.
Use enough mayonnaise to coat good. Cut eggs in quarters.
Chill.
When ready to serve, cover platter with lettuce, garnish with eggs, green onions and radishes cut in roses.
Serves 6 to 8.
If want to fix for large group, increase all ingredients.

title: double-chocolate fudge squares
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour and soda.
Set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup chocolate pieces and vanilla and stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a medium bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth. Stir in remaining chocolate pieces and the nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool completely on wire rack.
Cut in 16 squares.

title: flo's quick tantalizing jello salad dessert
directions: Follow directions on Jell-O boxes to prepare Jell-O and mix together.
Combine pineapple and cream cheese; mix well.
After Jell-O has begun to thicken, fold cream cheese mixture into it.
Do not stir.
Pour mixture into serving bowl.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet potato dessert
directions: Cream the white sugar, salt, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla in the mashed sweet potatoes. Make the topping from the last 4 ingredients. Pour topping over top of mixture and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Top with either dry bread crumbs or dried onion rings.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish or casserole dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jello salad
directions: Put pineapple in saucepan with sugar; heat until boiled.
Put Jell-O and 2 cups cold water.
Add 1 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup nuts.
Mix with Jell-O mixture.
Let set, then spread Cool Whip, rest of cheese and nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: worcestershire chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Put slice of margarine on top of each.
Cover all generously with Worcestershire sauce.
Cover tightly.
Cook at 300° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
If a lot of liquid is left when uncovered, put back in oven uncovered for a few minutes more.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach with salt and sugar.
Drain and add eggs, cheese and mushroom soup.
Season with garlic salt to taste.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix dates, crackers, baking powder and 1/2 cup sugar and nuts together.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold the dry ingredients into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: punch
directions: Combine in a gallon jug the Kool-Aid, sugar and pineapple juice.
Fill just rest of way with water.
When ready to use, pour in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In medium bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: ambrosia bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/3 cup confectioners sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in 3/4 cup margarine until crumbly.
Press into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, eggs, chopped pecans, coconut, 1/4 cup flour and baking powder in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Spread over baked layer.
Combine 2 cups confectioners sugar, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix until smooth. Spread over cooled layer.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into bars and top with pecan halves.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: louis stiles' winning cherry marshmallow dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk slowly; cool.
Take out 1/2 cup vanilla cookie crumbs to reserve for later.
Put butter in remaining crumbs and mix.
Press in bottom of pan.
Whip cream until stiff, then fold into marshmallow and flavoring.
Put into pie crust.
Pour cherries over top.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top of cherries.

title: sweet potato casserole*
directions: In medium bowl, beat potatoes and milk until smooth.
Blend in yogurt, eggs, sugar, spices and pepper.
Add walnuts.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in 1 tablespoon of oil in frying pan until white. Shred chicken.
Saute chicken, peppers and onions in 1 tablespoon of oil until onions are hot.
Remove from pan.
Add 1 tablespoon of chili powder and 1/2 salt.

title: swiss steak(electric skillet)
directions: Combine flour with salt and pepper.
Pound mixture thoroughly into both sides of the steak.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: pumpkin banana shake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into cups.
Makes three servings.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans and parsley.
Mix very thoroughly.
Form into ball and roll in pecans and parsley.

title: cinnamon rolls or better way rolls
directions: Pour warm water into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and yeast; let stand a few minutes.
Stir to dissolve.
Add salt, shortening and egg; stir.
Add half of flour and beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour and knead on floured board.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 30 minutes.
Form rolls in greased muffin tins or roll pan.
Let rise and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: coffee cappuccino
directions: Combine equal parts of each ingredient and serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, Bisquick mix, cheese and milk together. Roll out into marble shaped balls and bake about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 3 layers. Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Spread between layers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and oleo and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and
refrigerate.
Mix
instant vanilla pudding with milk and whip together.
Add
softened ice cream to whipped pudding mix.	Pour over crumbs
and
refrigerate.
Pour
Cool	Whip (8 ounces) over pudding
mixture
and
refrigerate	again.	Crush Heath bars with rolling
pin
and
sprinkle on top of mixture. Refrigerate until time to serve.
Put candy bars in refrigerator to chill before crushing.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine flour, butter, and 1 cup pecans.
Press mixture into a 9x13 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and set aside to cool completely.
With an electric mixer, combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar, and 1 cup Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour mixture over cooled crust.
In a bowl, combine pudding mix with milk.
Pour pudding mixture over cream cheese mixture.
Top chocolate pudding mixture with a layer of additional Cool Whip.
Garnish with additional chopped pecans and cherries.
Keep dessert in refrigerator; serve chilled.
Yield: 24 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes. Insert toothpick to check for doneness.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender for 30 seconds.
You may also add fresh fruit.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together adding pecans last.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 425° for 10 minutes and 350° for 25 minutes.

title: navettes sucres(sugar shuttles)
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into a bowl.
Add butter, egg yolks and vanilla extract; knead until dough is well-blended.
Chill for 2 hours, then divide the dough into portions the size of a small walnut.
Roll each piece of dough with the palm of your hand on a lightly floured board to give it the shape of a sewing machine shuttle.
Dip each in the egg whites and roll in sugar.
Bake on a lightly buttered baking sheet in a moderate oven (350°) for about 8 minutes or until the cookies are lightly brown.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Saute onion in a little butter.
Add remaining ingredients except ham.
Simmer 1/2 hour or so.
Add ham and heat through.

title: easy hot fudge cake
directions: Combine flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, sugar, oil, milk and nuts together.
Put that in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and remaining cocoa and sprinkle that over batter mixture.
Pour the water over top of this layer.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: happiness
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle liberally with "Ha! Ha!".
Serve at once with a sweet smile.
Make plenty for seconds.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Break cake into large pieces, then layer ingredients as listed in a punch bowl.

title: spanish chicken
directions: In a big pot, brown onion, garlic and chicken in olive oil. When translucent, add chicken broth and tomato sauce. Next, add salt, pepper, paprika, a splash of red hot pepper and parsley flakes. Let simmer for 2 hours (don't lose juice). Shred the chicken. Add 2 cups uncooked rice. Let simmer another 1/2 hour or until rice is cooked.

title: hamburger rice balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Place in baking dish and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied citrus peel
directions: Let peel stand overnight covered with water; drain.
Bring six cups of water to boil.
Add peel and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Drain and repeat with another 6 cups of water.
Drain.

title: baked beans and meat
directions: Brown meat and onions in butter.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Add meat.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 20.

title: chewy bread
directions: Melt the margarine; add sugar and mix, then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and nuts and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: white grape juice tea
directions: Bring water to a boil and pour over tea bags.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags; add sugar, white grape juice and unsweetened lemonade flavored drink mix.
Stir well.
Serve chilled.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: steak sandwich
directions: Saute onion and mushroom with dash of garlic salt.
Cook sliced bite size steak in separate pan.
Butter buns and brown. Cook gravy per package directions.
Layer on bread the steak, onion, mushrooms, gravy, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.

title: tea time tasties
directions: Cream together cream cheese, flour and butter.
Make small balls and put in miniature muffin tins.
Mix eggs, butter, brown sugar, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Saute beef and onion in large skillet; drain off fat.
Combine sauce, garlic, basil, salt, oregano and broth.
Spoon half over meat mixture.
Layer cottage cheese.
Pour boiling water over noodles; let stand 1 minute to soften.
Place over cottage cheese. Spoon remaining sauce over.
Cover.

title: chili crisps
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: 4~b's old fashioned cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine chicken base, water, butter, chopped onion and sugar. Simmer until onions are clear.
Add tomatoes, baking soda and stir well.
Add cream, liquid creamer and heat to serve.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: cornbread
directions: In a medium bowl, mix buttermilk and egg whites.
In larger bowl, pour in cornbread mix and stir until smooth; mix in egg-buttermilk mixture.
Blend together.
Pour into greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, white sugar, flour, soda and salad oil. Remove 3/4 cup for topping to which add 1/2 cup nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Set aside.
To remainder, add 1 egg, vanilla, buttermilk, soda and baking powder.
Mix well and pour into 2 round cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: new york steaks
directions: Preheat barbecue on high.
Mix all ingredients (except steaks) in a deep plate.
Place steaks in plate and marinate for 15 to 30 minutes.
Place steaks on hot grill and cook 8 to 10 minutes depending on taste.
Turn at least 3 times, baste and season.

title: rich and cheesy broccoli
directions: Saute crackers in butter.
Butter casserole dish.
Layer broccoli, cheese, crumbs, ending with crumbs.

title: polish sausage stuffing
directions: Brown sausage; remove from pan with slotted spoon (the sausage has been removed from the casing).
Place in bowl and add bread and seasonings; drizzle milk over it.
Saute celery in butter until soft.
Stir into mixture.
Stuff in bird.
Delicious when cooked on Weber Grill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soups and water; set aside.
In a buttered baking dish, layer beans, potatoes and onions.
Pour half of soups on top of these.
Place browned beef over this and pour remaining soups over this.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cheese popovers
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese, in container of electric blender.
Cover and blend for 30 to 40 seconds, scraping sides, if necessary.
Fill heated and greased muffin pan half full.
Place a cube of cheese in center of each popover.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 dozen popovers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in pan; stir in brown sugar to melt.
Remove from heat and drain pineapple (save 2 tablespoons of juice).
Press pineapple slices into brown sugar; set aside.
Beat egg yolks; add white sugar, beating well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg yolk mixture.
Add pineapple juice and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until glossy.
Fold into yolk mixture. Place in prepared pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix together, make patties & fry.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish with butter.
You will need a 9 x 13, extra deep dish or 2 (8 x 12) regular dishes for this recipe.
Break angel hair pasta in half and place in boiling saltwater until almost done.
In large bowl, mix chicken broth, soup and dry Italian dressing.
Melt Velveeta cheese and pour into mixture.
Drain pasta and place into mixture with chicken and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish(s).
Sprinkle top with dried bread crumbs until covered.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour or until mixture starts to bubble on top.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together in mixing bowl, then put in oven at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave sweet potato pie
directions: Mix spices with boiling water.
Place into sweet potatoes. Add sugar, eggs and butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in milk. Place in microwave until thickens, stirring occasionally.
Place in pie shell and bake at 425° until pie shell browns.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick and yellow.
Stir in zucchini. Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add walnuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Cook fryer until tender.
Remove from bone.
Cut into pieces. Saute onion in margarine until clear.
Combine chicken, onion, soups and broth.
Heat but do not boil.
Stir in sour cream and chilies.
Put a layer of Doritos in bottom of large casserole dish. Pour half of mixture over Doritos.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over mixture.
Put another layer of Doritos over this and pour remaining chicken mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.

title: salmonettes
directions: Pour juice in can and set aside.
Mix egg and drained salmon. Mix good and when gummy, add the flour; stir in thoroughly and mix well.
Will be thick.
Do not add salt or pepper.
Mix 1/4 cup of the salmon juice with baking powder and beat with a fork.
After it foams, pour into salmon mixture and mix.
This time the mixture will be thin.
Drop by small spoonfuls into deep fat.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil one quart water, cloves, cinnamon and allspice together for five minutes.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover pan and let cool completely.
Add two quarts water, sugar, orange juice and lemonade.
Stir together .
Makes three quarts.

title: bombe dessert
directions: Remove ice cream from the freezer to soften.
Preheat conventional oven to 325°.
Place the sliced pound cake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dot with butter and bake until the butter is melted.
Remove from oven and sprinkle generously with Amaretto while it is still warm.
Arrange in serving bowl.
Add the softened butter pecan ice cream to cover the pound cake.
Add the can of crushed
pineapple, with or without liquid, depending on your choice.
Sprinkle the cereal with a heavy hand and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage leaves in 1/4 cup water and place in a covered dish in the microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until limp; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place approximately 1/3 of mixture at stem end of each leaf.
Roll leaf around mixture, tucking in sides.
Place cabbage rolls, seam side down, in colander.
Put 1/4 cup water in dish below colander.
Cover and microwave on High 7 minutes.
Rotate 1/4 turn.
Microwave until beef is done, 8 to 9 minutes longer.
Let stand, covered, for 1 minute.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with graham crackers.
Put a layer of sliced bananas, a layer of sliced strawberries and a layer of crushed, drained pineapple.
Pour prepared pudding over layers. Layers can be repeated.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate for a few hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple in buttered cake pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Pour dry cake mix over cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Slice 2 sticks butter over top of cake mix.
When almost done, put coconut and walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Toss together and chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, then add bananas and nuts. Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef vegetable stew
directions: Peel and cube potatoes, onions and carrots; shred cabbage.
Put in large pot and cover with water.
Cook for awhile, then add roast (cut up), broth and tomato juice.
Season to taste.
Simmer for several hours.
You can add more water if needed.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is brown and onion tender. Drain. Add chili powder, cumin and salt. Stir well. Cook meat mixture over low heat 10 minutes. Spoon meat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer beans, tortillas and cheese over meat mixture.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over cheese.
Spread soup over top of casserole. Cover baking pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit surprise drink
directions: Put ingredients into blender.
Blend until it foams.

title: porc a'la normande(roast pork, norman-style)
directions: Put the pork (fat side up) into a roasting pan with the onions cut
into
4ths and a fraction of each sage leaf on top of
them. Season and pour round the cider.
Roast in moderate to hot
oven at
400° for 1/2 hour.
Lower the heat and roast for 30
minutes to the pound, basting with the hot stock from time to
time. After
the
meat
has been cooking for about 1 hour, add
the unpeeled but cored apples to the pan around the pork,
each
one heavily
sprinkled
inside
with
nutmeg and cinnamon.
When the meat is cooked, remove to a warmed serving dish.
Arrange the apples and onions around it, and keep warm.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil elbows for 15 minutes in salt water. Drain elbows.
Mix all ingredients together, stirring constantly.
Pour in baking pan or bowl.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until brown. Makes about 8 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Stir in flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour marshmallows over top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes at 350°.
Frost.
Refrigerate (can be frozen) cake before cutting.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pans (batter looks soupy).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 3 loaf pans.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, confectioners sugar, egg, almond extract and vanilla. Stir in flour and salt.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish and vegetables on top. Do not salt. Pour soups that have been beaten together over vegetables. Bake, covered, 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into square dish and freeze.
Cut into squares.

title: helen's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add lemon juice and bananas. Sift together dry ingredients and pecans.
Mix well, but do not beat or overmix.
Place in three small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Quickly stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until solid (about 5 minutes).

title: black bottom cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make filling.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, 1/8 teaspoon salt, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 egg with electric beater until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Next, make the batter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into loaf.
Put into baking pan. Combine the following ingredients and pour over meat loaf.

title: cheesy sausage biscuits
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat until browned.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Top with enough stuffing to cover top, then sprinkle melted butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Dissolve
soda in buttermilk and cook slowly with sugar and butter.
Cook until when tested mixture forms a soft ball.
Cool. Add flavoring and beat.
If icing becomes to hard, add a little hot water.
Makes enough for 3 layer cake.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, ground raisins, chopped nuts, stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Line muffin pan with pastry and fill with mixture.
Bake until light brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy blueberry delight
directions: Melt margarine and combine with flour and pecans. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Top with blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: banana fritters
directions: Heat oil to 350°.
Wrap banana with lumpia wrapper and fry until lumpia wrapper cooks.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: beef skillet supper
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, salt, nutmeg and milk.
Mix together thoroughly and form into 6 patties.
Set patties aside.

title: penny's old time fudge
directions: Bring to boil; boil until forms a ball in cold water.
Remove form heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir (to speed up cooling process, place pan in cold water to harden).
Pour into plate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles (use 1 teaspoon of oil for no sticking).
Chop artichoke hearts.
Chop broccoli and slice radishes.
Drain noodles and add mayo, Zesty Italian dressing and all other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Great for summer!!

title: honey bars
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well, then add egg and chopped nuts. Press by hand into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given, except for tortilla chips. Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Dough:
Combine 1 stick margarine, cream cheese and flour.
Mix well.
Take marble-sized amount of dough and press evenly into tart pans.
Put 1 teaspoon of crushed pecans in bottom of each pan.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, sauerkraut, mustard and onion.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crumbled corned beef, cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over all and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Blend all of the ingredients until smooth.
For best results use an electric blender.
Spread evenly in casserole dish.
Top with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, chopped black olives and freshly shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: white icing
directions: Beat Crisco and butter or margarine.
Alternate warm milk, sugar and vanilla until thick for spreading.
Delicious on devil's food cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over the chicken in casserole dish.
Crush 1 1/2 rolls of Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Take 1 stick of oleo (low salt).
Melt and pour over crackers. Bake at 325° to 350° until mixture bubbles and is golden brown.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl and add pie filling.
Beat with wire whisk; let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and chopped candy.
Freeze for 6 hours or overnight.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Heat strawberries and Jell-O (no water).
Let cool.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
In large bowl, layer wafers, sour cream mix and strawberry mixture.
Repeat layers until bowl is full.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine milk, onion, butter, soup, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine all ingredients (except cheese) and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: marble bark
directions: Microwave the chocolates in separate medium microwavable bowls on High 2 minutes or until almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time. Stir until chocolates are completely melted. Stir 1/2 cup walnuts into each bowl.
Alternately spoon melted chocolates onto wax paper lined cookie sheet or tray. Swirl chocolates together with knife to marbleize. Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Break into pieces.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Sift together into bowl flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add shortening, 2/3 cup milk and flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add another 1/3 cup milk and the egg whites.
Beat 2 more minutes. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake until cake tests done.
Cool.
Put cooled layers together with pineapple filling, spreading about 1/2 cup over center of top layer.
Frost sides and a 1 1/2-inch border on top with a fluffy white icing.
Time:
Layers 30 to 35 minutes, oblong 35 to 40 minutes, both at 350°.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Mix
crushed crackers and melted margarine; reserve 1/2 cup for top
of dessert.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: beefy baked bean casserole
directions: Cook beef and onions until brown, stirring to crumble the meat.
Drain.
Combine the meat mixture with the remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rhino pot roast
directions: Cut rhino into bite size pieces.
This should take about 4 weeks.
Add enough brown gravy to cover; add vegetables.
Cool in a large kettle over a campfire for about 2 weeks.
Serves about 2,000 people, but if more are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added, but please, do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find "hare" in their pot roast.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° until bubbly.
Makes a large amount.

title: deviled almonds
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add almonds and fry, stirring constantly, until nuts are golden. Remove from oil; drain. While warm, sprinkle with celery salt, salt and cayenne pepper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add flour.
Fold in eggs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Separate chicken wings into 3 pieces.
Discard tips.
Marinate wings in ingredients that have been heated until the sugars dissolve.
Cool.
Add wings and marinate 24 hours.
Remove wings from marinade.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Brush occasionally with marinade.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bacon.
Shape mixture into 5 to 6 small loaves. Wrap each loaf with a strip of bacon.
Place loaves in baking pan and top each with catsup. Cover pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Pour soup mix in pan with drained spinach; let absorb, then mix in sour cream, mayonnaise and onions.
Serve with pieces of rye bread.

title: holy smoke cake
directions: Combine margarine, flour and chopped nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread over top of cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk; spread over cream cheese layer.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix sugars and water, stirring until dissolved; boil for 1 hour.
Remove from heat; add instant coffee, vanilla and vodka. Store in tightly sealed bottles or jars for 2 weeks before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from each can and mix well after each can.
Mix all ingredients well with low-fat Cool Whip.
Place in the refrigerator in a bowl and let set for 10 to 15 minutes.
Ready to serve 4 to 6.

title: geraldine's italian meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, diced onion, seasoning, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Mix with hands until well blended.
Divide mixture to form 2 smaller loaves (1 large loaf can be made or second loaf can be frozen).
Place loaf into casserole or roaster.
Pour remaining sauce over meat loaf and add water until mixture is about 1-inch high.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
If desired, add potato cubes and carrots around meat loaf during last hour.

title: tomato jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add can of stewed tomatoes. Pour into bowl or flat dish.
Refrigerate to set.
Garnish with mayonnaise or Miracle Whip before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, peppers and onions; drain fat. Layer in casserole dish the hamburger, macaroni, pizza sauce, cheese, pepperoni, etc. Finish with a layer of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Stem, clean and pat dry as many very large, fresh mushroom caps as you want for "horse-dovers."
(Save the stems to cut up and use in soup or gravy.)

title: crabmeat spread or dip
directions: Combine the cream cheese, lemon juice, garlic powder, chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce and Miracle Whip or mayonnaise. Spread in the bottom of a very shallow dish; refrigerate until firm (about 1 hour).
Spread cocktail sauce on top of the cream cheese mixture, leaving approximately 1/2-inch edge around outside.
Sprinkle crabmeat over cocktail sauce.
Sprinkle fresh parsley over crabmeat.
Chill for a couple of hours.
Serve with Triscuits or strong chips.

title: freezer rolls
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a large bowl.
Heat milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and flour to make stiff dough.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Punch down and put on floured board.
Knead lightly.
Pinch off dough and put in well buttered pan.
Freeze or let rise and cook in hot oven at 400° until brown.

title: nutritious poppin' fresh cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except 1 cup flour, oats, nuts, wheat germ and coconut.
Beat at medium speed until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
By hand, stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Crumble meat in pan with oil, onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft and clear.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 5 cups of sauce.
It can be frozen for later meals.
Also, can be made by mixing meat, parsley and Italian cheese into meat balls, then cooking with onion and oil the same as above.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove the crust from bread and set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken, cover with mushrooms and water chestnuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs. Blend in milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange cheese on top.
Combine soups and pimientos; pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, crumble crust. Toss with melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili soup
directions: Fry hamburg and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add bananas.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients. Stir into
banana
mixture.
Add
nuts.	Bake
in
greased and floured loaf pan one hour at 350°.

title: bun's pumpkin pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: holiday fruit balls
directions: Melt oleo, marshmallows and milk over low heat.
Mix together remaining ingredients except coconut.
Pour over dry ingredients. Mix well.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Makes almost 200 balls.
Can freeze.

title: christmas salad(makes 8 x 13-inch pan)
directions: Step 5:
Mix and cool red jello in hot water; add cold water. When cool, pour on top of cream cheese layer; partly set.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: ham and asparagus bows (light)
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling water in a large Dutch oven according to the package directions, except add the frozen asparagus or broccoli during the last 5 minutes and the ham during the last minute of the cooking time.
Drain and return to the pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Stew chicken, cool and remove skin and bones.
Cut into bite size pieces (season stew water with salt and pepper when cooking chicken).
Cook rice.
Stir together chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise, soup, rice and almonds.
Put into 9-inch square baking dish.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: party sail boats
directions: Clean celery, then cut into serving size pieces.
Spread softened cream cheese on each celery piece.
Cut cheese slices with 4 triangles per slice.
Place a cheese triangle upright in the cream cheese.
(This is the boat's sail.) Place raisins on cream cheese.
Chill.
Serve.

title: steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Brown steak.
Cut in pieces.
Place in baking dish.
Top with onion soup mix (dry).
Add mushroom soup with water.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°, then bake uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: duffie fried squirrel
directions: Use only
young squirrels for this recipe.
Skin squirrel and cut into pieces.
Dip in batter made from beaten eggs; salt
and pepper to taste.
Roll in flour until well covered. Cook
in skillet.
Start off with real hot grease until brown, then	cut heat
to
simmer;
cover
with lid and simmer until tender. Remove
squirrel
from
pan
and make gravy using the drippings, flour
and	milk.
Goes well with biscuits to sop. Serve with baked or mashed potatoes and a salad.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt margarine and mix with croutons.
Put on bottom of dish. Mix
other ingredients and pour over croutons.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy to make hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a large container.
Use 1/3 cup mix per cup.

title: pennsylvania dutch style noodles
directions: Fill large stockpot with cold water; bring to a boil.
Place noodles in pot and cook until soft.
Meanwhile, melt butter until brown.
This is called noisette butter.
Place aside.
When noodles are done, strain through a colander.
Pour noisette butter over noodles and stir.

title: salsa chicken with peppers(makes 4 servings.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large oven bag; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add salsa to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Add chicken to bag.
Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange chicken in an even layer.
Place pepper rings over chicken.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 half-inch slits in top.
Bake until chicken is tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
To serve, stir sauce; spoon over chicken.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix soup, squash, sour cream, carrot, and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In buttered casserole dish, put a layer of cornbread dressing mix; pour squash mixture over it.
Top with layer of bread crumbs, and dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp on the barbecue
directions: You will also need 12 bamboo or steel skewers (15-inch works best).

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread thinly on the tortilla. Roll up and wrap in Saran wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/4 inch thick and place on platter.
Serve with salsa.

title: nestle oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and Nestle butterscotch morsels.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cornflakes and margarine. Place in baking dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
In a large skillet cook chicken strips half at a time in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until no longer pink.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and cook until tender, but not brown.
Remove skillet from heat.
Add broth, uncooked rice, oregano, paprika, salt, pepper and saffron or turmeric.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, sweet pepper and frozen peas.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Stir in cooked chicken.
Cook and stir about 1 minute more or until heated through.

title: taco seasoning
directions: Mix together.
Seal airtight.
Use with 1 to 2 lb. ground beef.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup water.
Bring to boil and simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture begins to bubble.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Add cheese; mix well and set aside.
In a large skillet, saute ham and onions in 3 tablespoons butter until onions are tender.
Add eggs (beaten). Cook and stir until they begin to set.
Add mushrooms and cheese sauce.
Mix well and pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt remaining butter.
Toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Extra onions if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients. Add food coloring, if desired. Store in refrigerator until 15 minutes before serving. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix and bake in moderate oven until slightly browned.
Reserve a few crumbs for top.
Press crust into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meat sauce
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked ground beef. Cook 2 hours with lid on; uncover and cook 2 hours longer on low or simmer.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple glazed ham balls
directions: Combine ham, rolled oats, eggs, brown sugar and cloves; mix well.
Shape into ball; chill.
In large frypan, lightly brown ham balls in a small amount of shortening.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together in mixer for 4 minutes, then add coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then put on topping.

title: boone tavern spoon bread
directions: Stir
meal
into rapidly boiling milk.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and allow
to
cool.
The
mixture will be cold and very stiff.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and butter. Beat
with mixer
minutes.
Pour
into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake with frosting
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and beat for 8 minutes. Pour into 2 (9-inch) well-buttered cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool before frosting.

title: best coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on the back of the box to bake cake.
After baking the cake, pierce the top of it with a knife.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk on top; let it soak in.
Put Cool Whip on top of that, then add the frozen coconut.

title: sour cream-cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and 1 cup hot water in blender.
Mix until liquid is smooth.
Dissolve both packages of Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add cranberry mixture and pecans to Jell-O.
Put half the mixture in 8-inch square pan; chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over the top of chilled mixture.
Add second half of Jell-O over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: summer berry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix berries.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.

title: kraut salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Cover and chill for at least 8 hours.

title: anise cakes
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until very light.
Add baking powder, anise oil and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop a teaspoonful on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Roll crackers until fine.
Add sugar to crackers.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into dry ingredients.
Add almond extract and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch pie pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening.
Remove chops to a greased baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add carrots.
In saucepan, combine lemon juice, honey, onion, soy sauce, bouillon and half the pineapple syrup.
In small bowl, mix remaining pineapple juice and cornstarch until smooth; stir into lemon juice mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thickened; pour over chops.
Cover; bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Add pineapple chunks; top each chop with a pepper ring.
Bake, covered, 10 minutes longer.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and brown in oil.
Add 3 quarts water and cook until meat falls off bone.
Remove, cool and pick off chicken from bones.
Discard bones.
Add raw vegetables to broth and simmer, uncovered, until beans and potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add chicken and seasonings.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg on top.
Bake until golden brown.
Test with a toothpick.
When it comes out clean, take out of oven.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir cake mix with cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two (9-inch) pans.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: turkey or chicken 'n stuffing bake
directions: Combine oleo and water until oleo melts.
Pour over Croutettes; toss lightly.
Stir in 1/2 can onions.
Spoon stuffing mixture into a 9-inch baking pan (1 1/2-quart).
Press stuffing mixture across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell. Combine soup, milk, turkey or chicken and peas.
Pour into stuffing shell.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: smoked sausage with cabbage, sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Mix chicken broth, mustard and mustard seed in deep 12-inch skillet. Bring to a boil.
Add sweet potatoes and onions.
Then on medium, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add sausage and cabbage.
Then cover and cook about 15 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Stir in apple.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes until apple is crisp-tender.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion in microwave in margarine until tender. Add all ingredients to potatoes.

title: peach or apple pudding(cobbler style)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place sliced fruit in bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Toss together lightly with Bisquick and spice.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan or 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.

title: feather rolls
directions: Combine in a large bowl, 2 cups of flour, yeast, mashed potatoes, oil, sugar, salt and warm water.
Beat 1/2 minute on low speed
and
minutes on high.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate at
least
hours
or up to 3 days.
Punch down. Turn out
on
lightly
floured
surface.
Let rest 10 minutes. Shape into 24 rolls.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and let rise
until
doubled.
Bake
at 400° for 16 to 20 minutes.

title: 6-week bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt together in large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Store in covered container in refrigerator (up to 6 weeks).
Bake at 400° in muffin pans for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not freeze batter.
Bake as needed. Do not stir when you want to bake more muffins.
Very good!

title: almost instant rolls or "beat and bake rolls"
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake in 6 or 8 muffin pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy as pie crust
directions: Mix together flour and salt.
Use pastry blender to cut in shortening until pastry looks like coarse meal.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons at a time of cold water over mixture.
Stir with a fork until the dough follows the fork around the bowl.
Divide in half and chill.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: aunt wilma's pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle flour and spices on raisins and pecans.
Mix together.
Add vinegar last.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add other ingredients and mix until smooth. Grease and flour three bread pans. Divide batter into 3 pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Sift together cocoa and powdered sugar.
Combine bourbon and corn syrup.
Stir bourbon mixture into cocoa and sugar.
Add vanilla wafers and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Dredge in powdered sugar.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Put 2 layers of each:
crushed wafers, pie filling and whipped cream.
Top with crumbs from wafers and freeze.
Serve cold.
(Can be frozen overnight.)

title: lavista pizza dough
directions: In large mixing bowl or on dough board, mix flour, salt and sugar.
In 1/2 cup of warm water, dissolve yeast.
Add to flour mixture with oil.
Knead and mix well.
Let rise 1 hour in bowl, covered with white cloth.
Knead again and let rise again.
Makes 2 large or 3 or 4 small pizzas.
Water is added as dough is mixed.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all but blueberries.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325° in greased and floured Bundt pan. Cool for 15 minutes.

title: chili tomato macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat. Add water, macaroni, tomatoes, chili powder and seasoning mix. Simmer uncovered 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: apple dapple
directions: Beat oil and eggs together.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt twice and stir in oil and egg mixture.
Add vanilla, pecans and apple to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Put in 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix in soup well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread onion rings on top.
Return to oven to brown onion rings, about 3 to 5 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in oil in heavy skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir-fry, on medium high heat until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Lower heat, cover and let cook for about 12 minutes more.
Serves about 4 people.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt. Cover; cook 5 minutes.
Uncover.
Cook gently until the mixture begins to brown ever so slightly in the middle.
Remove from fire; add soda, maple flavor and nuts.
Pour into buttered flat pan, like a cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Delicious. Recipe used for many years.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over this and out to edge of bowl to seal.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan shortbread cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add flour and cornstarch; mix well.
Cover bowl (not metal) and chill 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in pecans.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten each ball with bottom of glass (dipped in powdered sugar).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove immediately from sheet to cool.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes. Mix together remaining four ingredients and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 225° for five minutes.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450° for about 30 minutes before serving. Wash potatoes thoroughly; cut each potato in quarters.
Place in large roasting pan with oil and remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle garlic powder to taste.
Toss to coat well.
Roast potatoes 20 minutes or until fork-tender and golden brown, stirring potatoes halfway through cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: olive spread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve on wheat or oat bread.

title: apricot casserole
directions: Mash apricots (drained); save juice to moisten.
Add brown sugar and crushed crackers.
Add enough juice to moisten.
Mix all together and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Great!

title: loaf(fern obergfell's recipe)
directions: Grind the almonds and potato chips together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in an oiled loaf pan and bake 45 minutes.

title: hot wings from charleston
directions: Cut wings from drummettes and loose piece from wing.
Place in sink or bowl in single layer.
Sprinkle Old Bay seasoning on chicken.
Place in deep fryer until done.
Melt butter in pot on stove in Texas Pete sauce (about 1 tablespoon of butter).
Soak wings in sauce until desired taste.
(The longer they sit in sauce, the hotter they are.)
Add water to sauce if it is too hot.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips or on fajitas as a salsa. May also be served over lettuce as a Mexican salad.

title: shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done but firm.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Mix shrimp, green beans, onion and pimiento in 3-quart bowl.
Blend oil, lemon juice and spices thoroughly in small bowl. Pour over the mixture of shrimp and vegetables.
Add macaroni and mix to coat all ingredients.
Seal and refrigerate overnight. Keeps for days.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add baking soda, sour cream and vanilla, beating to combine.
Beat in eggs, two at a time with one cup of flour; repeat, using all eggs and flour.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Cool, remove from pan, frost with favorite icing or leave plain.

title: orange caramel fudge
directions: Put 1 cup sugar in heavy saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is melted and golden brown. Add hot water and stir until sugar is dissolved. Add remaining 2 cups sugar, milk and salt.
Cook over low heat to 242° or until candy forms almost a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Candy will appear curdled.
Add butter, orange rind and nuts.
Beat at once until creamy.
Pour into greased dish. Cut into squares.
I leave out the orange rind.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over crust and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown each meat separately.
Drain well.
Press excess grease on paper towels.
Return meat to skillet and add cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Add seasonings and spread on bread.
Cut in triangles or circles.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Transfer to plastic bags when frozen.
Remove from freezer as needed and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Stir in brown sugar, bacon, tomato sauce, chili powder and water. Add to cooked onion. Cook 5 minutes on simmer setting, covered with lid.
Stir rice evenly into mixture. Cover and cut off heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: 1 dish meal
directions: Cook squash in salt water, drain.
Saute meat and onion.
Add rice, uncooked, and seasonings to meat.
Place 1/2 zucchini in bottom of casserole.
Cover with meat mixture.
Spoon cottage cheese over.
Add rest of zucchini.
Spread soup over mixture. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: krispie fudge sandwiches(microwave)
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
In microwave, melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in large Tupperware container.
Melt on Medium-high (not High).
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir well.
Press half of mixture in pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Melt remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix well.
Spread on mixture in pan. Spread remaining butterscotch Krispie mixture on top.
Press down lightly.
Remove from refrigerator 10 minutes before cutting.

title: norma's cheesy veggie casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Drain well.
Combine vegetables, celery, onion, mayonnaise, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper and pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine crackers, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup melted butter and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries until tender.
Add dry jello to hot berries, no water.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over double boiler to prevent scorching.
Melt slowly, then add noodles and peanuts.
Spoon out onto wax paper into little spoon size stacks.
Let them dry.

title: "fried" chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place butter and oil in large baking pan (about 9 x 13-inches) and set in oven to melt butter.
(Watch carefully, so butter does not burn.)
Combine bread crumbs, flour, salt, black pepper and cayenne in paper or plastic bag.
Roll chicken all over in melted butter and oil, then shake pieces, one at a time, in bread crumb mixture until coated.
Shake off excess coating, then place chicken, skin side up, in baking pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in center of oven until coating is browned and crisp and chicken is cooked through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple with juice and baking soda.
In a large bowl combine cake mix and remaining ingredients.
Add pineapple mixture and blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on a rack.

title: salad dressing(like french)
directions: Put all ingredients into jar and mix well.
Refrigerate until all used.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons sugar.
In top of double boiler, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Beat in 1 whole egg and 3 yolks; reserve 3 egg whites.
Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly 10 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
In bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole, spoon 1/2 cup custard; cover with wafers to fit.
Top with generous layer of sliced bananas; pour 2/3 cup custard over bananas.
Arrange wafers around outside edge of dish; cover custard with wafers.
Top with sliced bananas and remaining custard.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Pour into serving dish and chill until firm.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese and sugar; mix until smooth and well blended.
Spread over top of salad and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: s.r. special
directions: Saute bell pepper with meat.
Add eggs and season.
Cook slowly.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in mixing bowl.
Add salt and pepper and chopped vegetables; stir well.
Stir in Ranch dressing until moist.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix together. It will be thick (like dough). Press into 9 x 13 buttered or sprayed pan or glass dish.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple, sugar and water to a boil in a large deep pan.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
When jello mixture is lukewarm, add cream cheese and beat until cream cheese is blended.

title: buckeyes or peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and make into balls. Place on wax paper.
In a double boiler, combine chocolate chips and paraffin.
Melt together until runny.
Put a toothpick into balls and dip each one into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper until cool.

title: perfect pumpkin cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, thoroughly beat first 3 ingredients. Mix in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat.
Mix in walnuts (optional).
Bake in lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan or a Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 7-9 layer vegetable salad
directions: Layer ingredients in serving dish in order given. Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first ingredients in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Then top beans with bacon slices. Bake on 350° for about 45 minutes until liquids are thick and bacon is cooked brown.

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Soak the bread crumbs in the 1/2 cup milk.
Drain.
Mix in the onion, egg, meat and seasonings.
Shape a giant burger.
In a large nonstick pan, brown the bottom of the "burger" (3 minutes). Drain off the grease.
Turn the burger over.
Add the spaghetti sauce (you may not need all of it).
Cover and cook 15 minutes. Add the cheese.
Cover.
Cook a minute or two more, until cheese melts.

title: beverly's meat loaf(moist and wonderful!)
directions: *Can use a can of turkey rice soup in place of the tomatoes and celery.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg and beat well.
To flour, add soda, cinnamon and salt. Sift together. Add apples alternately with flour mixture. Beat well.
Stir in raisins and pecan meats. Bake 45 minutes in 300° to 325° oven in 9 x 9 pan.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
(Reserve small amount of powdered sugar for top of cake.) Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining powdered sugar over warm cake.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add corn and egg.
Add melted butter. Mix well.
Drop in deep hot fat with teaspoon.
Fry 8 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk; beat until smooth.
Spread over cheese filling, then spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle chopped nuts.

title: chocolate banana cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in chocolate bits and vanilla.
Sift flour, powder, salt and soda together.
Add alternately with the mashed bananas.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oven porcupine
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix hamburger, rice, 1/2 cup water, onions, salt, garlic powder, pepper and celery salt.
Shape mixture into tablespoon size balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover, bake for 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed until thick and lemon colored.
Add butter and next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: white banana nut bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and beat mixture well.
Sift flour and measure.
Add salt and baking powder; sift again.
Add dry ingredients gradually and mix well. Add chopped nuts.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Mix next 4 ingredients with gelatin mixture.
Place in a ring mold.
Turn out onto a tray.
After placing on the tray, fill center of mold with cool whip.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes. Top with onion rings, cracker crumbs, etc.
Bake another 15 minutes uncovered.

title: cheesy chowder
directions: Cook veggies in butter until tender.
Add pepper and broth. Simmer 30 minutes.
Blend flour and milk.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and 1/2 cup of grapefruit juice.
Mix cornstarch and salt with 1/4 cup of grapefruit juice and stir into boiling water and sugar.
When thick, remove from fire and add egg yolks, first stirring some of hot mixture into them.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: grandma's chicken fricassee
directions: Paula and I collaborated on this recipe, and it was fun.
This dish is quite different from my usual fare, but my wonderful wife said it is popular in mill towns.
I'll list it under vegetables, but it could be used as a main dish.
Try it, I think you will be quite pleased.

title: sante fe soup
directions: Brown ground beef, drain or rinse off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Combine and add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake until lightly brown, but little soft. They will puff up, then flatten with crinkled tops.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange peanut butter cake
directions: Grate peeling from oranges.
Reserve orange peels and cut into bite-size pieces and drain well.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, eggs, peanut butter and cinnamon.
Mix according to package directions.
Stir in orange peel and pieces.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serve warm or cool.

title: cocktail ham biscuits
directions: Wrapped Olives:
Roll stuffed olives in half slices of bacon. Secure with toothpicks.
Broil until bacon is crisp.

title: tuna bake
directions: Cook shells. Heat soup and cheese together until melted. Combine shells, vegetables, cheese sauce, tuna, 1 cup fried onions and seasoning.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: domenic's roast and potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. On stove top, brown roast and onion in small amount of olive oil in roasting pan. May need to use both front and rear burners at the same time. Add all other ingredients. Bake for 5 to 6 hours checking, turning so roast doesn't dry out. Serve with corn and green beans and ice tea.

title: chili(like wendy's)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix beans and sauces.
Add ground beef and chili powder.
Simmer for several hours.
(I use a crock-pot.)

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Beat into mashed potatoes, cream cheese and butter.
Mix in sour cream.
Mix together milk, eggs and onion.
Mix with mashed potatoes and put in greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with foil and put in refrigerator.
Next day bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut. Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain most of juice from can of clams.
Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon and olives.
Put in casserole.
Top with the olives and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach rockefeller
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch square pan.
Put in slices of tomatoes.
Sprinkle tomatoes with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Mix rest of ingredients together and place over tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares when hot and serve.

title: heavenly cranberry salad(no cooking)
directions: Combine raw cranberries that have been ground in a blender and 1 cup sugar.
Let stand 2 hours.
In second bowl, whip whipping cream and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Add mini marshmallows and let stand 2 hours in refrigerator.
Combine the mixture; add 1/2 to 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup drained, crushed pineapple.
Let stand, covered, in the refrigerator overnight.

title: apple cinnamon swirls
directions: Heat
oven
Melt butter in baking dish;
heat water and
sugar slowly until sugar melts (can be done on low heat while preparing dough and apples).
Mix flour and shortening.
Add milk
and
stir
until dough leaves side of bowl. Turn
out
on floured board and knead.
Roll dough out into a large
rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle apples evenly over
dough
and sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Roll dough up like
a
jelly roll. Slice dough into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in
pan with melted margarine.
Pour sugar syrup around rolls. Bake for 40 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Add oats and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool thoroughly, then peel off paper.
Store in cool place.

title: jello whip
directions: Mix jello according to directions on box.
Allow jello to begin to set in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple together.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple mixture to slightly jelled jello.
Partially jell this mixture.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Keep refrigerated.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Mix next 6 ingredients and beat with a fork or wire whisk until thick and well blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss thoroughly.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.
Can be made ahead.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: barley soup
directions: Peel and dice the carrots, celery and potatoes.
Cut the leeks and cabbage leaves into fine strips.
Saute the vegetables and soup bone in the butter.
Add the barley.
After a few minutes, pour in the bouillon.
Stick the onion with the clove and add to the soup, along with the bacon.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove the soup bone and onion from the soup.
Mix the egg with the cream; add to the soup.
Heat, but do not boil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients, except wheat flour, together in bowl. Stir in wheat flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add beaten egg and milk into dry mixture.
Stir only until all flour is moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen, approximately.

title: meryl's lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk thoroughly.
Fold in Cool whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mom's cherry pie(mrs. verneda wangler)
directions: Pour cherry juice from cans into pan.
Heat juice until it boils, then lower heat.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a bowl. Pour some cherry juice into the mix to make a thickening, then pour mixture into pan, stirring slowly.
Mix mixture with remaining juice.
Stir until well mixed and almost thick like pudding.
Add cherries to mix, then pour into pie shell.
Add butter on top of cherries, then place top layer of pie crust over it.
With tip of knife, puncture a few small holes on top.

title: braised celery and carrots
directions: Cut
celery
hearts
and
carrots in matchstick pieces. Melt butter in a large, heavy skillet or saucepan.
Add celery and carrots.
Stir
to	combine
and
coat
with
butter.
Add chicken broth,
salt
and
pepper.	Cover and cook over medium heat about 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables can be pierced with a	fork. Carefully
turn
celery hearts and carrots once during cooking. Remove
vegetables to a warm serving platter. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: magic bars
directions: Mix together the butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: glazed ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Before baking pour in the glaze.

title: *raisin cookies
directions: Place raisins and water in a saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for about 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool; do not drain.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and add sugar, beating well.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in the raisins with liquid and vanilla.
Gradually add the flour mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.

title: thick and chewy chocolate bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add flour and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir together broccoli, eggs, onion, butter and cottage cheese.
Add corn muffin mix.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashion barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan and cook until thick.
You may want to add a chopped onion during cooking process for more onion flavor.

title: lemon herb sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; pulse until combined.
Add salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.
Pour over freshly steamed asparagus and serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour and all other ingredients.
Mix and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: turkey gyros
directions: Spread cheese on flour tortilla.
Add lettuce and turkey. Roll up and cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices.
Will make 5 or 6 slices per tortilla.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You will also need 24 cupcake liners.

title: low-fat chili(quick)
directions: Chop pepper, onion and garlic very fine.
Put tomatoes, chopped pepper, onion and garlic in a microwave covered dish. Microwave at 100° for 9 minutes.
In a large frying pan, cook turkey, adding cumin, oregano, chili powder, pepper sauce and cider vinegar as you stir.
Break up meat chunks as they cook. Add cooked vegetables to frying pan, mixing with meat mixture. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chop suey
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. oil in wok, add:
boneless pork loin, cut into long, thin strips, finely chopped ginger root.
Cook and stir until meat is no longer pink (2 minutes)
Set aside meat in bowl.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and flour; cook until thick.
Add half of hot mixture to beaten egg yolks and mix gradually into remaining mixture.
Add margarine and vanilla; cook until very thick.
Pour into shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add 2 tablespoons sugar and continue beating until very stiff. Spread over pie filling and bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses and let soften. Form into balls or logs and roll in paprika.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Soak raisins in hot water while preparing cake.
Drain before adding.
Cream the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add applesauce; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Mix well.
Batter will be heavy.
Fold in drained raisins and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce into bite-size pieces; place in bottom of large bowl.
On top of lettuce, put the peas, then water chestnuts, etc., finishing with the green onions.
At this point, there should be six layers of vegetables.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Boil pork until tender, remove fat and bones.
Shred pork and add other ingredients.
Cook for about 3 hours on low heat until thick.
Add water when necessary.
Can use beef or leftover ham or roast chicken.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and raisins; mix well and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Put beef and all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover and cook.

title: apple crunch
directions: Cream together sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter. Place apples in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: nicole's favorite
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl in order listed and stir well.
Chill overnight.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cut up apricots.
Put in water to cover, boil and simmer 15 minutes until soft (may need extra water).
Mash with fork.
Add lemon juice, cornstarch and sugar.
Mix well; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Stir constantly; cool about 15 minutes.
Pour and spread over crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet over medium heat, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, eggs, cornstarch, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Stir in cheese, onion and ground beef.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: party meatballs
directions: Meatballs:
Combine all ingredients.
Shape into small balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes; cut in 1/8 pieces.
Brush with butter; add salt, pepper and seasoned salt to taste.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice in 1 cup water until absorbed (stir often).
Add 1 quart milk.
Cook until thick.
Add 1 quart milk, sugar and raisins.
Cook until thick.
Add another 2 cups milk; cook 10 minutes.
Mix in vanilla and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9-inch pie crust and bake for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, crumble bread.
Pour milk over; stir to mix well.
Add sugar, melted oleo and vanilla.
Mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven until done and tan on top. Cool and cut in squares or just eat it hot.
Anyway it is good. You can use leftover biscuits instead of bread.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix ingredients except Hershey bars and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt Hershey bars over double boiler and spread over peanut butter mixture.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, add oil,eggs and vanilla.
Do not use mixer.
Stir only until ingredients are moistened.
Fold in pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Spoon into three 9-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rich and creamy frosting
