directions: Place the sugar, margarine, cream cheese and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix well with an electric mixer until smooth.
With dull table knife, carefully spread the frosting over the top and on the sides of the cake.

title: ham delights
directions: Split party rolls open.
Spread top and bottom with blended mixture.
Add ham to rolls and top with cheese.
Wrap tightly in tin foil in the aluminum roll trays.
Heat for 10 minutes at 400°. Can freeze before cooking.

title: easy rhubarb cake
directions: Evenly place sliced rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb, then cinnamon over sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix next.
Melt butter and drizzle over everything.

title: green beans with toasted pecans
directions: Cook beans in boiling salted water 5 minutes, drain. Meanwhile cook 1 small sliced red onion in the butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
Add the beans, pecans salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lentil salsa soup
directions: Put olive oil in soup pot. Set on medium heat. Stir in garlic, onions and carrots; stir constantly until the vegetables are soft, not brown. Add water, lentils, red salsa and salt. Cover; let come to boil, then reduce heat so it bubbles without boiling hard. Stir occasionally and cook for 45 minutes. If too thick, add more water.

title: potato chip cookie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, vanilla, potato chips, and pecans well. Add flour and mix.
Drop by tablespoon and bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: fall salad
directions: Combine greens, apples and celery.
Shake dressing; pour over salad.
Add cheese and toss lightly.
Garnish with nuts.

title: rich baked beans
directions: Use Dutch oven if not cooking on reflector oven for foil cooking.

title: red's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with mixer until well blended. Add the milk and mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill with milk; chill.
Prepare according to freezer manufacturer's instructions.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade,
condensed
milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into cracker crusts and refrigerate.

title: easter holiday ice cream jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Add well drained fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in sliced banana.
Pour into a pretty clear crystal bowl and chill several hours before serving.

title: hot curried fruit compote
directions: In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, arrange fruit.
In a small bowl, mix sugar with curry powder.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over fruit.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Brush pan liquid over fruit occasionally.
Serve fruit warm.
Is good served with ham or baked chicken.
Makes four servings.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Saute beef, mushrooms and onion until meat is browned.
Mix in spices.
Add tomato sauce; simmer about 30 minutes, covered.
Stir in ripe olives, if desired.
Cool.

title: quick and easy spaghetti(crock-pot)
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet. Pour into slow cooker. Add remaining ingredients to cooker. (If you cook your spaghetti, do not add at this point.) Cover and cook on low 4 hours. If you cook your spaghetti separately, serve sauce over spaghetti.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Boil sugars, corn syrup and water 5 minutes.
Add maple flavoring to suit your taste.
Cool and store.
This will not crystallize if kept in the refrigerator.

title: grandma's chocolate sauce
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with enough milk to make runny.
Add margarine.
Cook over medium heat until it boils.
Simmer on low heat until creamy.
Pour over hot biscuits.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in 2-cup microwavable bowl; microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir.
Microwave on High 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes more or until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda and pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet to cool.
Break into pieces. Makes 10 cups.

title: orange muffins
directions: Grind orange rind, pecans and raisins together in food processor.
To mixture, add and "whirl" a little the flour, soda and sugar.
In microwave, melt margarine.
Add buttermilk.
(Heat 20 to 30 seconds to take off chill.)
Add eggs and beat.
Add wet mixture to dry mixture; stir as little as possible.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Then beat in the eggs. Then add the molasses, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Roll into balls and dip in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all together very well.
Put into a nonstick pan.
From the time it starts cooking, time it for 20 minutes, no longer.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Cut each chicken breast half into 8 pieces.
Mix oil, garlic and pepper with chicken pieces and marinate about 30 minutes.
Combine bread crumbs and cayenne. Place on plate.
Roll chicken pieces in bread crumbs and place on large cookie sheet in a single layer.
Bake for about 15 minutes, until browned and cooked through.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or casserole. Crumble 2 cups of cornflakes; mix with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Put on top.
Buttered crumbs may be used.
Ham may be added.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pork steak casserole
directions: Soak rice in cold water for 1 hour.
Cut steak in pieces and put in bottom of casserole.
Add rice.
Cook tomatoes, onion and salt until onion is soft.
Pour over steak and rice.
Add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly rolls
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar, then add boiling water; set aside and allow to cool.
In a small bowl, dissolve the yeast with warm water; add this to cool mixture and beat together.
Add egg and salt and beat into mixture.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough, but not runny dough.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Pick the bits of shell from the crab meat.
Pour lemon juice over crab and put in bowl in refrigerator.

Cream the cheese and continue to beat, adding all other ingredients except the crab. When mixture is smooth, add crab and refrigerate until ready to serve. When time to serve, heat, then put in chafing dish and serve with crackers.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box, adding 1/3 cup milk and margarine.
Put half of batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk. Pour over warm cake and add chips and nuts.
Pour the remaining batter on top and bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until done.

title: white feather biscuits
directions: Sift flour with salt, sugar, baking soda and baking powder. With a pastry cutter or hands, blend the butter into dry ingredients.
Use cold butter so that dough doesn't become greasy. Mixture should resemble coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and stir with a wooden spoon until dough is well mixed, about 1 minute. Turn out onto a floured board and knead for 1 minute longer until dough is smooth.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Put biscuits on parchment-lined baking sheet (or cover with aluminum foil).
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes until biscuits have risen and are slightly golden. Makes 20 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Makes 2 cups of dressing.

title: kay's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and butter that has softened. Gradually mix in the dry ingredients (flour, soda and salt).
Add the vanilla and almond extracts; beat well.
Fold in the chocolate chips and nuts.
(Caution:
This is a very thick dough.)
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix in order listed; do not mix cheese!
Sprinkle half of cheese on mix in hot, greased skillet.
Add remaining mix and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: syrup tea cakes
directions: Bring syrup, sugar and shortening to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined pan and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: apple raisin nut cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix together sugar and oil.
Stir in self rising flour. Add grated apples and mix well.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Batter will be lumpy.
Place batter into an ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Prepare topping.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Work in shortening, egg and milk.
Put as many blueberries as you wish, I put 1 1/2 cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all and process until smooth.
(I like a little chunky.) Pour into buttered
casserole.
Bake
at
350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve
warm
in chafing dish.
(Good with crab meat added.)

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, soup, grated cheese and mushroom soup in large Pyrex baking dish.
Crush corn flakes and mix with butter. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tasty turkey pot pie
directions: Combine salad dressing, flour, bouillon and pepper in medium saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thickened.
Add turkey and vegetables; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.
Unroll dough into two rectangles.
Press perforations together to seal.
Place rectangles side-by-side to form square; press edges together to form seam.
Cover turkey mixture with dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: depression fruitcake
directions: Stew raisins in water until 1 cup liquid remains.
Cream sugar and butter; add raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda, salt and flour. Mix and bake in a loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: favorite cheesecake
directions: Pour evaporated milk into bowl and cool in refrigerator.
Also chill beaters.

title: cornflake squares
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and cook for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter until mixture of coarse crumbs forms.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of crumb mixture. Sprinkle remaining mixture over bottom of baked pastry shell.

title: bebe's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook on low heat for 1 hour. Great for pig pickins!
Makes 2 gallons sauce.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in hot oil in 12-inch skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Arrange vegetable in a shallow baking dish. Top with chicken slices.
In a small bowl, blend soup and wine.
Pour over all. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: frosting and filling for angel food cake
directions: A bought angel food cake is fine.
Slice cake into 3 layers. Put filling between layers and on top and sides.
Frozen strawberries can be used instead of pineapple.

title: baked cream cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line baking sheet with foil. Sprinkle dill, black pepper and garlic salt on both sides of cream cheese. Unroll crescent rolls to form a rectangle. Place cream cheese in center of crescent rolls. Wrap around cream cheese sealing ends. Place on baking sheet seam side down. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with additional dill. Bake at 350° 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter; add water, flour, salt and sugar.
Mix well. Add pecans and vanilla.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Make balls; roll them in coconut.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken to make marinade.
Pour into baking dish with chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pauline's soup
directions: Mix.
Bring to boil; stir constantly for 30 minutes.
(Note: Cook beans 15 minutes before adding.)
Pour in jars and seal. Makes 22 pints.
Process 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: company oatmeal
directions: Combine oatmeal and milk; let rest 15 minutes.
Mix apple with lemon juice and sugar; set aside.
Chop and add remaining fruits. Combine oatmeal with 1/2 of fruit and 1/2 of whipped cream.

title: hamburgers and cake
directions: Put on cooking hat.
Squish with hands.
Then put them in the oven to cook.
Take it out with hands.
Then get green and red paper and dry it off.

title: hot potato dish
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper and drain.
Combine hamburger mixture with cornmeal mixture.
Grease 7 x 11-inch pan.
Pour mixture in greased pan. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter flavoring and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes and eggs; beat well.
Combine all dry ingredients and gradually add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces.
Place in crock-pot. Pour mushroom soup (without water), onion and bacon bits over steak.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.
Serve over hot, buttered noodles.

title: chicken and broccoli pie(pie makes its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under running water to thaw.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese, the chicken and onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
You can use 2 packages or frozen chopped broccoli and omit the chicken.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lefse
directions: Heat water to boiling and add margarine until melted.
Pour over potato flakes, dry milk and salt.
Beat until smooth, then cool overnight.
When ready to roll out, divide dough in half and add 1 3/4 cups flour to the first half.
Mix well by hand.
Make into a long roll and cut into 15 portions.
Roll each lefse out with a grooved rolling pin, using as little flour as possible. Keep mixture cold.
Have the grill as hot as possible.
Bake quickly for a tender product.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oblong dish.
Mix peaches with 1 cup of sugar, peach juice or water to make 3 cups of liquid.
Heat thoroughly. Mix remaining sugar, flour and vanilla; add milk or water to make batter and pour over oleo.
Pour peaches on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Cook 1 minute or 45 seconds after it begins to boil.
Let cool by itself.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until smooth.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add mayonnaise and cottage cheese.
Add the grated cucumber, chopped onion and pimento, mixing well.
Pour into mold or glass dish and congeal.
Serves 8 to 10.
Great with meat or other salads.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 11-inch pan (greased) in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Shred dried beef into bottom of rather shallow
greased casserole dish.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each chicken breast and place on top of beef.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Sprinkle with mushrooms.
Blend undiluted soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 275°
for 3 hours.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Stuff chilies with cheese.
Beat the yolks until they are lemon color.
Then beat the whites until stiff, adding one heaping tablespoonful of flour with salt.
Fold with yolks.
Dip stuffed chilies in batter and fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Serve with finely cut lettuce, chopped tomato and taco sauce.

title: beef con queso dip
directions: Brown beef. Drain.
Add onion and brown. While cooking, add Ro-Tel, soup, pepper and cheese.
Bring to slow boil.
Serve while hot.
Makes about 2 quarts. Can be stored in refrigerator or frozen for later use.

title: easy stuffed squash
directions: Prick squash several times with fork.
Parboil about 10 minutes. Remove from heat; drain and cool. Slice in half.
Scoop out the meat of the squash onto separate plate.
Add crumbled bread, grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mixture back into squash boats.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.
Sprinkle on paprika to color.

title: cauliflower parmesan
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat in 1-inch boiling water, heat cauliflower and salt to boiling.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, until fork-tender.
Drain well.
Place whole cauliflower in a serving dish.
Pour melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle well with cheese, then with seasoned pepper.

title: mocha chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and beat.
In a small bowl, mix buttermilk, cocoa and soda. Stir until cocoa dissolves. Add to creamed mixture. Beat.
Add flour and then add vanilla. Divide into 3 layers. Cook at 375°.
Let cool before trying to handle.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Spread rice over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle half of seasoning packet over rice.
Lay skinned chicken breasts on this and sprinkle remaining seasoning over chicken.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, saute onions in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes, covered.

title: chinese new year cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch pieces in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir occasionally until smooth. Remove from heat; stir in nuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper covered cookie sheet.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in an airtight containers.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Whip Ricotta cheese, add 3/4 cup sugar, then add 3 egg yolks. Add milk and vanilla.
Beat in egg whites.
Fold in chocolate. Pour into pie plate with Pillsbury pie crust in the pie plate. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: marge's zucchini salad
directions: This recipe makes more dressing than you will need. Refrigerate the leftover dressing for other uses.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix soup mix and flour; stir in milk.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish; bake 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: meat balls
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Shape into balls.
Cook in frying pan over medium heat for 20 minutes, or until done.
Add to sauce.

title: raisin pie
directions: Wash raisins and pour boiling water over them.
Let simmer while mixing the cornstarch, sugar, salt, lemon juice and oleo. Pour this mixture over the raisins.
Pour mixture into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until golden brown.

title: saltine cracker crunch candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a large saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, coconut, crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into buttered pan and chill. Cut out squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except raisins and nuts; mix until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 60 to 65 minutes in 350° oven; remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add desired amounts of onions and green peppers. Drain meat. Add Ro-Tel, chili, Velveeta and whipping cream. Simmer all ingredients for 30 minutes. Serve over tortilla chips.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat together with beater until smooth and pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Then cover with the icing.

title: jello angel dessert
directions: You need a large bowl with top (as big as the cake).
Slice bananas; cover the bottom of the bowl.
Set angel food cake over bananas.
Put the remaining bananas in the ring of cake.
Make Jell-O.
Pour over cake.
The cake will rise so be sure to put top on firm.
Refrigerate to harden.
Slice to serve.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "fudge" very creamy(willie mae bridges)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except margarine, vanilla and nuts). Boil until syrup forms a soft firm ball when small amount is dropped into cold water.
Stir constantly while boiling.
Only stop stirring while testing for soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine.
Do not stir.
Cool until lukewarm.
Beat until creamy. Add vanilla and nuts.
When it loses its gloss, pour into greased square pan.
(You can sprinkle small marshmallows in bottom of pan before pouring mixture.)

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: never fail cheese souffle
directions: Cube firm bread (French bread is best).
Place in bowl with milk, salt, cheese and eggs.
Place in buttered casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: high tech chicken
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole with dried beef.
Wrap 1 strip bacon around each chicken breast half.
Place in casserole. Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover casserole with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1 hour longer.

title: layered salmon salad
directions: On a large platter, layer the ingredients in the following order:
tofu, salmon, tomato, onion, bean sprouts, watercress and 1/4 of the green onions.
In a saucepan, combine the salad oil and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add the shoyu and the remaining green onions.
Mix well.
Pour the dressing over the salad and serve immediately.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix together. Then layer in order listed.

title: sloppy joes for 100
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown the beef, onions, peppers and celery in batches until all meat is browned.
Remove with a slotted spoon to a large roaster.
Add the next eight ingredients. Cover and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve on buns.
Makes 100 servings.

title: famous pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for filled one-crust pie, using 9-inch pie pan.
Mix filling ingredients in order.
Pour into crust.

title: fudge
directions: Place sugar and evaporated milk in large saucepan.
Bring to boil for 13 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place rest of ingredients in large bowl.
Pour milk mixture over other ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into large pan.
Refrigerate until candy is set.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into loaf and bake in moderate oven about 1 1/2 hours.
Decorate top with bacon curls, green pepper rings and fresh mushrooms, sauteed in butter.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Slice bacon in half lengthwise and wrap each half around bread stick in a spiral fashion.
Line a glass baking dish with 3 thicknesses of paper towels.
Place Bacon Sticks on top.
Cover with another paper towel to avoid splattering.
Cook on High in microwave for 9 to 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix together the pineapple and jello.
Boil for 2 minutes and then cool.
Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip into pineapple and jello mixture.
Congeal overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce, bread crumbs, slightly beaten egg, onion flakes, salt and pepper; mix well.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, brown sugar, parsley flakes and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Pour over loaf and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Line tube pan with heavy brown paper and grease pan.
Let cake stand in pan overnight.

title: life recipe
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flour with gifts of love.
Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith to lighten.
Let rise to height of happy living.
After pouring this into your daily life, bake well with human kindness. Serve with a smile.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Stir all ingredients in order given. Pour into 2 greased floured loaf pans. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven. While still warn brush on glaze topping.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cheese and add cool whip and marshmallow creme.
Mix well. Chill until needed.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat
together sugar, syrup, salt, flour and eggs.
Add vanilla,
butter
and
pecans.
Pour
into	unbaked pie shell. Bake in a slow 300° oven for 1 hour or until set.

title: bev's baked haddock
directions: Place haddock filets in a greased shallow baking dish.
Cover with the slices of cheese in a small bowl.
Mix together the soup and the milk until smooth and pour over the cheese slices.
Mix together the melted butter and Ritz crackers and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: red pepper preserves
directions: Chop the peppers and chilies fine in a food processor. Combine the sugar and vinegar in a deep, heavy-based pan and heat to dissolve sugar.
Add peppers and chilies and bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in pectin and return the mixture to a boil over high heat.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Keeps for about 1 year.

title: queso dip
directions: Mix well and cook in double broiler, microwave or slow cook until cheese is melted.
Stir, let cool and serve with chips.

title: delight
directions: Cut marshmallows in pieces.
Dissolve in cream, then whip as it thickens.
Add pineapple juice and other ingredients.

title: chicken breasts piquant
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: cheese cake cups
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs. Put papers in cupcake pan.
Place vanilla wafer flat side down in each.
Fill cup 3/4 full.
Bake 350° for 18 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding grahamwiches(children will love these.)
directions: Pour milk into large mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in whipped topping and marshmallows.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Mix first seven ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Stir together cinnamon, glue and water.
Mixture should be as thick as cookie dough.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Sprinkle cinnamon on your work surface.
Spoon chilled dough onto cinnamon. Knead dough until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut shapes with cookie cutters. Dry shapes on wax paper at room temperature, turn them over twice a day for 4 days.
Can be baked on cookie sheet in warm oven for 2 hours.
Before dry, poke a hole in each one with a plastic straw.
When dry, add ribbon hangers. Ornaments will shrink.
Can be painted or leave natural.

title: laura lindler's chicken salad
directions: Stew chicken until tender, remove from bone and grate in food processor.
Toast almonds with tablespoon of margarine until golden brown.
Mix all ingredients well with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce.

title: crockpot deer meat stew
directions: Add all the ingredients place in crockpot.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: see's fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk together for 11 minutes.
Turn out fire and add chocolate chips, marshmallows, butter and vanilla.
When all is melted, add nuts as desired and beat.
Spoon into mounds on wax paper or into greased cake pan and cut into squares.

title: politician's delight(aka the next best thing to robert redford)
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine and flour until crumbly.
Add walnuts. Spread and pat down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
(It will look the same after baking.)
Cool thoroughly.

title: savarin
directions: Drain mandarin oranges, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Heat juice water to boiling, then add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.

Cool and refrigerate just until the thickness of unbeaten egg whites. Blend in pudding until smooth. Add drained mandarin oranges (save a few for garnish) and undrained pineapple. Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Pile gelatin into mold.
Chill for several hours until firm.
Garnish with mandarin orange sections, grapes or other fruit.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Mix tomatoes, beans and chili powder.
Simmer.

title: snow pudding
directions: Soak the gelatin in 1 cup cold water.
After dissolved, pour in boiling water, then add sugar and vanilla.
When congealing, beat in whites of 6 eggs (after they have been stiffly beaten). Serve with grated coconut sprinkled over and whipped cream on top, then a cherry for "dress up."

title: kay's rice broccoli
directions: Cook 2 cups water and 1 cup rice for 20 minutes (not instant, regular rice).
Mix mushroom soup and chicken soup together. Thaw broccoli.
Layer rice, soups, broccoli and top with Cheez Whiz. Use lasagna type pan. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shake the biscuit pieces in a Bundt pan, layering on top of each other.

Pour left over cinnamon and sugar mixture into a sauce pan and add margarine and vanilla. Melt over medium heat and when hot, pour over layered biscuits. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove. Cool for 3 minutes and then invert onto a dish.
(Do this at the right time or it will stick to the pan.)
Eat with fingers.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatine and all remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold greased with mayonnaise or Pam spray.
Chill until firm and serve with crackers.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat with onions in a pot. Cook until onion is tender and drain. Stir in remaining ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste, if desired. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: tropical salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in bowl and refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add pecans. Cook 20 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally. Drain on paper towels. Mix remaining ingredients in paper bag. Add warm nuts to mixture in bag and shake to coat.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour. Blend well; add salt and pepper to taste. Gradually add milk. Stir until smooth. Add cheese until melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli, then mix 1/2 the cheese and all the mixture, except cracker crumbs and pats of butter.
Spread remainder of cheese on top in casserole dish.
Spread cracker crumbs on top and pats of butter on top of crumbs. Cover and cook at 350° until bubbles and crumbs are brown.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Cool.
Add walnuts and marshmallows; mix.
Sprinkle coconut on wax paper.
Spoon chocolate mixture into log form (on wax paper) and sprinkle coconut on top.
Wrap tightly and refrigerate.
Slice to serve. Makes 4 small logs.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Soak rhubarb and sugar together for 2 1/2 hours. Boil 5 minutes or so. Add crushed pineapple and juice; boil 3 to 4 minutes more.
Add the jello; stir well. (Just the jello without the water.)
Let set.
Not to be canned, just keep in refrigerator to use "for now".
This could be doubled once, but no more; it wouldn't work out well.

title: chicken and pasta stir-fry
directions: In a large wok, heat the oil.
Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir one minute.
Add spaghetti and heat through.
Add tomato and cook and stir 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Mix well.
Serve warm topped with chopped parsley.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well and set aside.

title: mike's famous lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly, add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in salted water; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place 1/2 the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread with 1/2 the cottage cheese filling.
Add the 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting in squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in a little garlic.
Remove bones and skin chicken.
Place chicken in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix broth, soup, onion, celery and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken. Place cornbread mix on top.
Place margarine around in different places on top of cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar until light.
Add eggs 1 at a time; add vanilla.
Alternately add flour and whipping cream.
Pour into a greased and floured pound cake or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool completely.
Enjoy!!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop onion and parsley.
Mix with other ingredients while macaroni is cooking.
When macaroni is cool, mix with rest of ingredients.
Best if made day before.
Serves 10 adults.
Great with a barbecue or for lunch with warm bread.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Layer 8 x 12-inch pan with pineapple, then pie filling. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Cook for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook and cool pie crusts.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add nuts.
Spread evenly half of mixture in each crust.
Spread pie filling on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread half of Cool Whip on each pie.
Refrigerate overnight.
(Cherry pie filling can be substituted for blueberry.)
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken breast
directions: Mix chicken, corn flakes and 1/4 cheese.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in a bowl.
Dip chicken in butter and coat with corn flakes and cheese.	(Salt and pepper to taste.)
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Combine ingredients together gently and carefully.
Using faith and vision, mix together with strong belief of the outcome, until finely blended.
Use thoughts, words and actions for best results.
Repeat.
Yields unlimited servings!

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together and add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350°, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan.

title: jean's popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, vinegar and water together.
Boil gently, without stirring, until hard "chick" ball forms when a portion is tested in a cup of cold water.
Add soda and butter; mix well while foaming.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: crescent chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onions. Spoon mixture onto separated unbaked crescent rolls.
Roll each one up with mixture inside.
Brush on margarine.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
For the sauce, mix sour cream and soup.
Heat and spoon over top of roll-ups right before serving.
Very Good!!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and bring to boil; remove garlic. Makes 1 cup.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef and mix well.
Add ground beef and mix thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and drain.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet. Combine soup, sour cream and water in bowl. Mix well. Layer thin sliced potatoes, parsley, onions, soup mixture and pork chops in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Add gelatin to water and dissolve.
Puree shrimp in blender. Barely heat juice from shrimp; stir with gelatin and add lemon juice.
Mix all ingredients together and add to shrimp in blender.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 1/2-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish; set aside.

title: baked chicken with chipped beef
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in bacon.
Layer chipped beef in bottom of 8 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over the top.
Can be refrigerated.
Bake, uncovered, in 275° oven for 3 hours.

title: quick beef dish
directions: Brown beef. Stir in onion and tomatoes. Add potatoes and El Pato chile.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are soft.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in milk.
Add oil.
Add liquids all at once to flour and beat until smooth. Bake on hot griddle or skillet until golden brown.
Yields 10 to 12 average size pancakes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine together sugar, flour or cornstarch and cocoa.
Mix milk and egg yolks.
Get this hot on medium heat.
Add sugar, cocoa and flour mixture slowly to hot milk.
Add vanilla, butter and salt.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato soup and kidney beans.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add cabbage, chili powder, soy sauce and water; simmer for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and eggs; beat well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift together salt, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Combine with banana mixture.
Add sour cream, nuts and chopped bananas.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: spinach and artichoke hearts casserole
directions: Saute artichoke hearts in butter and then combine with spinach, cream cheese and onion.
Put in casserole dish and top with Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad oriental
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, ginger, salt and pepper.
Add to chicken mixture.
Serve on crisp greens.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Serves 8.

title: fruit punch
directions: Do not dilute the juices.
Mix all and freeze except 7-Up or Sprite.
Just before you are ready to serve, pour 7-Up or Sprite over frozen mixture.
Real good for any kind of party or wedding.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix the jello and sugar as directed on box. Gel slightly and add the remaining ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tanners hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight containers. Use 3 rounded tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, egg, oats, soup and 3 tablespoons catsup.
Shape into loaf.
Place in crock-pot; put remaining catsup on top. Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve soda in applesauce and combine all other ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Heat the strawberries and Jell-O until the Jell-O is dissolved.
Let cool in pan of ice water with ice cubes until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar.
Add to strawberry mixture along with Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie crust and chill. Top off with extra Cool Whip.

title: saucy oriental pepper steak
directions: Brown chuck steak in oil.
Add garlic powder, soup and 3/4 cup of water.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add bell pepper and tomato wedges and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch, blended with 1/4 cup of water.
Bring to a boil. Simmer until thickened.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shrimp saute (garides yahni)(greek)
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain and put aside.
In a skillet, saute onions in olive oil. Add tomatoes and parsley. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 more minutes.
Preparation time:
45 minutes. Total cooking time: 30 minutes.

title: ice cream kolacki
directions: Soften butter, ice cream and cream together.
Blend in flour. Pinch off small pieces of dough; roll into a ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb into center of ball to make an impression for filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce with meat balls
directions: Make sausage into balls.
Combine ground meat with remainder of ingredients and make into balls.
Brown balls in small amount Crisco oil flavored with a little garlic and onion.
When brown, add 1 large can tomato puree (rinse can with water and add to pot).
Add 6 small cans tomato sauce, salt and 1/4 teaspoon oregano.
Add balls to liquid and cook at least 2 hours, the longer the better, the thicker.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In 2-quart baking dish, combine all ingredients except stuffing mixture.
After combined, add stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cottage meat loaf
directions: Combine in a separate bowl and mix well.
Spread mixture over the meat.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Drain off fat.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pound chicken, smooth side down. Put a slice of ham and slice of cheese on each piece of chicken. Roll from short end and close together with a toothpick. Combine egg, mustard and water. Mix well. In another bowl, mix Parmigiana cheese, salt, pepper and bread crumbs. Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in crumbs. Put in single layer in a greased casserole dish. Spoon 1 tablespoon melted butter over each rolled breast. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add bacon and other ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork tenderloin with peanut sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a small pan and heat until bubbly. Brush meat with peanut sauce and grill, covered, for 10 minutes. Turn meat and brush with peanut sauce again.
Cook until meat temperature reaches 155°.
Test meat for doneness.
Serve with lime wedges and additional peanut sauce.

title: easy salad
directions: Whip together the cream cheese, sugar and milk. Add the Cool Whip, nutmeats, pineapple and cherries.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar; set aside.
Separate biscuits and squash them into a muffin pan. Spoon mixture into each.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Beat the butter in a medium-size bowl with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in the 10x sugar and cocoa powder alternately with the milk until smooth and spreadable.
Add a little more milk, if necessary.
Spread evenly over the top of the cake. Garnish with nuts and orange slices, if you wish.

title: american chop suey
directions: Prepare all ingredients and measure all ingredients.
Heat the oil in a large skillet that has a lid over medium heat.
Cook the meat and onions in the oil until slightly brown.
Add the celery and green peppers.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add the rice, salt, water and flavoring.
Stir until the flavoring has dissolved.
Cover with lid and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally until rice is tender or about 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry ground beef, then pour off fat from meat.
Chop up meat until it's small.
Heat up baked beans on low heat, then add butter, brown sugar and meat to beans.
Let it simmer for about 3 to 5 minutes, then stir.
Taste and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix sugar and melted butter, adding beaten egg, yeast mixture and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Drop into well-greased muffin tins and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin-pecan biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut butter into flour mixture.
Stir in pecans.
In glass measuring cup, combine pumpkin and half and half.
Stir into flour mixture.
Dough should be stiff.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead several times.
If too wet to handle, add more flour.
Pat dough to 1/2 inch thick and cut with 2 inch cutter. Place on greased baking sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter and honey.
Makes 12 to 16 biscuits.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cool and dice.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream and curry; mix together well.
Add grapes.
Serve over bed of lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Empty peaches into greased rectangular baking dish.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, butter, vanilla and egg.
Drop by spoon onto peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: white cucumber pickles
directions: Fill quart jars with cucumbers.
Fill large part of jar with vinegar.
Add salt and sugar.
Add water to fill up the jar. Seal; put in open kettle and cook for 10 minutes.
Just simmer to make sure they are hot enough to seal.

title: sausage pies
directions: Saute
onion
and
green pepper in microwave.
Add sausage. Brown and drain well.
Lower heat.	Add Cheddar cheese. Add
eggs, well
beaten, evaporated milk, pepper, garlic salt and flour; mix real good.	Heat until it cooks thick.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: For crust:
Mix butter or margarine and graham crackers. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, broccoli, stuffing and rice.
Heat oven to 350°. First place stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place diced chicken and put slices of Velveeta over chicken.
Mix together broccoli, soup and rice and place over chicken and cheese.
Add more Velveeta over the top of the casserole and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven eggs
directions: Cube bread in a 2-quart greased 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Melt cheese and butter and pour over bread.
Beat eggs well with milk, salt and mustard and pour over bread.
Mix lightly with fork.
Let stand in fridge overnight.
Take from refrigerator 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken mushroom bake
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a paper bag.
Shake chicken strips in flour mixture until coated.
Melt butter in a large skillet; brown chicken on all sides in skillet.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream and mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender, uncovered.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven just until cheese is melted.

title: country breakfast
directions: Crumble sausage, brown and drain.
Put in a casserole dish. Add grated cheese, chilies, sour cream and mushrooms.
Pour eggs on top.
Spread hot sauce over top.
Bake at 400° until eggs are done.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cook until melted.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix dry ingredients together with fork; stir in egg and sprinkle over the top of pared and sliced apples (dotted with butter or oleo and sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon).
Drizzle the melted oleo over top of crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts and oatmeal.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 40 minutes or until apples are done and crust is brown.
You may also use this recipe and substitute fresh peaches.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients well together, except potato chips and cheese.
Put into 2-quart casserole and sprinkle chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix by box directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix with powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on cake mix.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: indian squash bread
directions: Blend together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir in all the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly by hand.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into two well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Keeps well in the refrigerator and freezes well.

title: pepparkakor (swedish ginger cookies)
directions: Sift flour, spices and baking soda together.
Cream the butter or margarine.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Add flour mixture gradually, beating until well blended.
Wrap and chill overnight.
Roll out a small amount of dough at a a time on floured board; cut with floured cutters.
Place about 2 inches apart on lightly-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: golden potatoes and franks
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese spread, onion and mustard; mix well. In lightly greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish, layer half of potato mixture and frankfurters.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with green onion slices, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: margaret's very easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add sauce and water (swished in jar). Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix 3 cheeses, eggs, parsley and seasonings in bowl. Spread 1/2 cup of sauce on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch glass casserole dish.
Layer 1/3 of noodles next.
Follow in order with 1 1/2 cups sauce, 1/2 cheese mix, 1/3 noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce, cheese, 1/3 noodles and rest of sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 more minutes, if needed.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Microwave the spinach while still in box for 6 minutes. Drain.
Microwave onion, mushrooms and garlic until cooked.
Add spinach and all other ingredients, except noodles and spaghetti sauce. Spoon some of the mixture onto each noodle; roll up.
Place in a 9-inch square baking dish. Top with spaghetti sauce. Microwave on 70% power for 12 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts in halves and bone.
Melt butter in skillet.
Mix flour, salt and paprika in paper bag.
Put chicken in bag; flour well.
Brown in butter.
Put ham in baking dish. Sprinkle diced celery over ham; place browned chicken over celery. Add remainder of flour to butter and blend well.
Add orange juice; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, sunflower seeds and bacon bits.
Mix until smooth, mayonnaise, vinegar and Equal.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over broccoli; toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Stir melted butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well with milk.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin and cream cheese roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Line with waxed paper; grease and flour the waxed paper.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg and salt onto waxed paper.
Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl until thick and fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients all at once. Pour into prepared pan; spread evenly with rubber spatula. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched with fingertip.
Loosen cake around edges with a knife.
Invert onto clean damp towel dusted with 10x confectioners sugar; peel off waxed paper.
Trim 1/4-inch from all sides.
Roll up cake and towel together from short side.
Place, seam side down, on wire rack; cool completely.

title: finger jello
directions: In large bowl, mix gelatine and Jell-O.
Add boiling water. Stir until dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm; cut into squares.

title: apple dip
directions: Melt the butterscotch morsels.
Mix with all other ingredients. Serve warm.

title: holiday ham spread
directions: Beat together all ingredients, except green and red peppers, until smooth.
Stir in red and green peppers.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain. Add Rotel tomatoes and Cream of Mushroom soup. Heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: wassail
directions: Make a light syrup of sugar,
2 cups water, red hots, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Strain.
Bring 12 cups of water to a boil.
Steep tea bags for 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk skillet cornbread
directions: Coat an 11 to 12-inch cast-iron skillet with nonstick spray. Set skillet in a 350° oven to warm.
Sift cornmeal into mixing bowl; set aside.
In a small bowl, mix baking soda, honey and buttermilk.
Add egg substitute and canola oil; stir to blend. Stir buttermilk mixture into cornmeal, adding a small amount at a time.
Pour batter into hot skillet and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cook for 30 minutes.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: In a 3-quart glass bowl, layer 1 1/2 cups chicken and the lettuce.
Combine rice, peas and parsley and spoon over lettuce. Layer with tomatoes, cucumbers, peppers and remaining chicken. Mix all remaining ingredients for the dressing and spread evenly over the top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish with pepper rings and parsley if desired. Toss just before serving.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix well.
Pour into crock-pot that has been greased with butter.
Cut several thin slices of cheese and place on top of mixture.
Sprinkle paprika or pepper on top if desired.
Cook 3 hours and 15 minutes on low.

title: walnut florentines
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour baking sheet.
Mix cream and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in flour and orange peel, blending well.
Blend in walnuts.
Drop batter by teaspoons onto baking sheet, spacing about 1 inch apart.
Bake until golden, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Transfer to wire rack; let cool.
Spread chocolate over half of the top of each cookie. Let dry on waxed paper.
Can be frozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: I ran across this recipe in our family cookbook and would like to put it in this cookbook in memory of my brother-in-law.
Out of the two boys, he was the one who enjoyed cooking the most.

title: molly's pizza sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Mix in 1 can tomato sauce and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir baking mix, egg and milk to a soft dough.
Spread half of dough in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour remaining can of tomato sauce over dough, spreading evenly.
Layer 4 slices cheese, meat mixture, mushrooms, remaining cheese slices and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: colorful kielbasa(makes 8 servings. prep time: 20 minutes.)
directions: In large skillet, combine soup, water and butter. Bring to a boil.
Add kielbasa and rice. Stir in peas, mushrooms and tomatoes. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand until cheese melts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken. Mix all ingredients together; top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break up angel food cake. Layer cake, fruit, pudding and 1/2 of Cool Whip. Continue layering until the bowl is full and top off with the other half of the Cool Whip.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: For best results, save the water that was used to boil the tenderloin in and use it for a base (no salt is needed then). Cook potatoes and carrots in stock (or water) until just tender; do not drain.
Cut pork tenderloin into small pieces and render over low heat in a medium saucepan.
Add onions and celery and saute 3 minutes.
Blend flour evenly into this mixture.
Add tomatoes gradually, stirring to keep smooth.
Add mixture to potatoes and carrots. Add clams, clam broth and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Freezes great too!

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all drained and cut-up ingredients together with mayonnaise.
Best if refrigerated 1 hour before serving to allow flavors to blend.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn and spread in very large sheet cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Cook over medium heat and boil for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove mixture from stove and stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Mix well and pour over corn.
Put in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool well and store in airtight container.

title: fried apple fritters
directions: Mix all together and deep fry; drain.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: aunt betty's irish oatmeal bread(1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, mix flour, oats, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, beat egg, honey and milk with rotary beater.
Pour egg mixture into oat mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, until crusty and cake tester comes out clean.
Turn loaf out on wire rack.
Brush top with melted butter.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, salt and margarine. After coming to a rolling boil, boil slowly for 10 minutes. Turn off heat. Add chocolate morsels and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer for 5 minutes. Pour into 3 buttered platters or pans. Pecans can be added if preferred. Makes 5 pounds.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon in a saucepan.
Remove from pan.
Saute pepper and onions in drippings until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Combine bacon, pepper and onion with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 4-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix yeast, salt, sugar and 2 cups flour.
Put flour mix into water; mix well. Add remaining flour to make a sticky dough.
Flip over in greased bowl and let double in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Roll out, using a little flour, to desired pan size.
Place on greased pizza pan and let sit 15 minutes.
Lightly brush top of dough with olive oil.
Bake on top rack of oven for 15 minutes at 400°.
Top as desired and finish baking for approximately 20 minutes.

title: cold roast pheasant
directions: Carefully wash and pat dry the outside of the pheasant. Remove the lungs and entrails from the inside cavity and wipe it well with a damp cloth.
Do not wash out the cavity, as it will take away some of the special flavor that is characteristic of game birds.
Mix together the salt, pepper and thyme.
If the thyme is fresh, chop fine; if dry, crush it against the salt with a spoon.
Sprinkle the cavity with half this mixture and add 1/2 stick of butter.
Rub the outside with 1 to 2 tablespoons soft butter and the rest of the seasoning.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in lard until crumbly. Add water and mix until it holds together. Knead 10 to 15 times until dough forms a smooth ball. Cover and let set 20 minutes. Divide dough into 2 parts. Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured board. Cut into 3-inch squares or triangles. Do not allow to dry. Cover those waiting to be fried. When ready to fry, turn upside down so that surface on bottom while resting is on top when frying. Fry in 3-inches of hot oil until golden brown, turning once. Add only a few at a time to maintain proper temperature. Drain on paper towels and serve immediately with honey.

title: cabbage wedges with creamed celery sauce
directions: Cook cabbage wedges, covered, in 1-inch lightly salted boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of liquid.
Place wedges in serving bowl.
Cover and keep warm.

title: date pudding
directions: Let 1 cup brown sugar, water and 2 tablespoons butter come to boil and set aside.
Cream together 1 tablespoon butter and 1 cup brown sugar.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Then add nuts and dates.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 liquid that was set aside into baking pan.
Drop above mixture by spoonful into liquid.
Then add remainder of mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix softened butter, powdered sugar, vanilla, flour and salt thoroughly. Mix in nuts. Chill dough. Roll into 1 inch balls. Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set but not brown. While still warm, roll in powdered sugar, while still warm, roll again. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Mix tomatoes and meat and simmer.
Cook noodles in water for 5 to 7 minutes and drain.
Mix noodles with meat and tomatoes and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients (except milk). Mix well.
Then slowly add milk; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked potato chips
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Use 2 baking sheets with sides (single thickness, not air-cushioned sheets).
Divide butter between baking sheets.
Melt in preheated oven.
Toss with onion, salt, pepper and potatoes, turning to coat.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash until tender.
Mash squash with a potato masher. In a large bowl combine sour cream, soup, shredded carrot and chopped onion.
Stir in squash.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and then butter or margarine. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix pumpkin, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, butterscotch chips and optionals.
Drop with teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 375°.

title: wilson's red velvet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 3 or 4 layers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Melt butter and mix with egg and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle over soup mixture and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add cheese and tomato sauce. Heat on stove or in microwave until smooth.
Add hot sauce to taste.
Serve with Fritos, nachos, etc.

title: zesty cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in mixer or blender.
Serve with crackers or as filling for celery.

title: coffee buns
directions: Melt
margarine and combine with all ingredients.
Beat until light
and
bubbly.
Add raisins.
Slowly add 2 1/2 cups of flour.
Knead
for
10 to 15 minutes.
If dough is sticky, add small amounts of flour.
Put in greased bowl and let rise in warm place until double in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down. Let rise again until double.
Form into small rolls.
Place on cookie sheet
and
let
rise
until
light, about 20 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine and pour over cucumber mixture.
Let come to hot boil. Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: taco dip
directions: Peel, pit and smash the avocados in medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
To assemble, spread bean dip in a large, shallow serving platter.
Top with seasoned avocado mixture. Layer sour cream and taco mixture, then sprinkle with chopped onions and tomatoes.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with taco chips.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
(Chill if desired.)
Roll on floured board.
Cut.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then mix and stir in next 3 ingredients.
Roll in small balls and then roll the small balls in 1/2 mixture of cinnamon and 1/2 mixture of sugar.
Do not grease cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: curd cheese cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Stir in curd cheese through a sieve.
Mix curd cheese, semolina, flour and baking powder.
Fold in the egg mixture.
Bake at 180°C for about 1 hour in a form pan.
When done, brush with melted butter and dust with powdered sugar.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place the ingredients in jars in layers.
Bring the following ingredients to a boil, then let cool slightly and then pour over the onions and pickles that have been layered.

title: brownies
directions: Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in large greased dripping pan.

title: wilma's favorite cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 1 dry vanilla pudding mix; bake as directed on cake mix in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix sugar and crushed pineapple; boil 5 minutes. Pour over hot cake.
Refrigerate cake until it is cold.
Slice bananas and spread over top.
Mix one box of vanilla pudding and put on cake.
Ice cake with Cool Whip, coconut and pecans.

title: festive chicken salad
directions: Cover breast with cold water in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain, skin and bone.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Blend mayonnaise and sour cream in medium bowl.
Stir in curry powder.
Mix in chicken, pineapple and walnuts.
Season with salt.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 2.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cut cheese into small chunks and add can of Ro-Tel.
Melt in microwave for 3 minutes, stirring every minute, until melted.
Fry hamburger and drain grease.
Add hamburger to the melted cheese and it's ready to dip your tortilla chips in!

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Add sugar, nutmeg, water, cinnamon and oleo to apples.
Make a top dressing of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour and mix to make consistency of bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake in slow oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: squash and apricot jam
directions: Peel, core and slice pears into small slices.
To each 5 pounds of pears, add 2 1/2 pounds of sugar.
Mix well and let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil, then cook very slow until juice has cooked down and the pears have turned light brown, about 3 hours.
Seal in jars.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Slice layers into 4 layers. Mix the coconut, Cool Whip, sugar and sour cream with a spoon, so not to break down icing.
Spread between layers.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Cook for 15 minutes after it boils, the first 3 ingredients. Stir in the jello.
Cook 5 minutes; pour in jars and seal.
(Can use sealing wax.)

title: chicken almondine
directions: Mix chicken, celery, rice, mayonnaise, chicken soup and onion and place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with corn flakes and almonds that have been sauteed in butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Fry sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly and brown.
In a large bowl, combine the sausage, cheese, pepper and biscuit mix. Add water; mix well.
Form into small, walnut size balls.
Place the balls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Can be served hot or cold.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: rich chocolate layer cake
directions: Note:
There are no eggs in this cake recipe.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Put in crumbled graham crackers.
Pour over pecans, raisins and cherries.
Mix well. Pour into a tube cake pan.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: chewy butter 'n nut clusters
directions: Mix cereal and nuts together in a large bowl.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine on medium heat.
Stir in sugar and syrup. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234° to 238°) on candy thermometer (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir in vanilla.
Toss over cereal and nuts.
Spread evenly onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Break into clusters. Store in airtight container.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in 3 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 small loaves.
Yield:
30 to 35 servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Place hamburger patty in large piece of foil.
Place onion slice on hamburger.
Cut up 1 potato and 1 carrot; place around hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Optional:
Can put catsup on hamburger patty.
Fold foil around meal.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fun rum balls
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except powdered sugar; stir until well blended.
Using a teaspoon of mixture for each, work in palm of hand and shape into balls.
Roll each ball in powdered sugar.
Store rum balls in tightly covered jar.
Makes 60 balls.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, eggs and mandarin oranges together and beat.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix pineapple and dry pudding well, fold in Cool Whip and set in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
Spread on cooled cake.
Keep cake in refrigerator.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Combine in a saucepan; cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Serve over steamed broccoli or cauliflower.

title: southwestern spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Add to Ro-Tel mixture.
Boil spaghetti noodles in water used for chicken.
Serve like Italian spaghetti.
You can cook chicken and spaghetti at the same time.

title: chocolate skillet pie
directions: Mix together sugar, egg yolks, cornstarch, cocoa and milk. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla and butter in iron skillet, then pour into baked pie shell.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, chocolate, milk and salt in 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Heat to rolling boil, stirring occasionally. Boil 1 minute, without stirring. Place pan of frosting in bowl of ice water. Beat until smooth and of spreading consistency. Add vanilla.

title: apple chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat the oil in the casserole pot.
Add the chicken and cook for 5 minutes, turning to brown.
Core and chop 2 apples and add to the casserole.
Add the apple juice and cook in the oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, drain. Add all ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes. Layer with noodles and cheese. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in an 8 x 12-inch pan. Place drained peaches in pan with melted butter.
Mix in bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Drizzle flour mixture over peaches and butter.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: yogurt
directions: Drain mandarins, puree in blender for 10 seconds.
Fold pureed fruit into the yogurt.
(For 8 ounces of yogurt, add 1/4 cup pureed fruit.)
Chill thoroughly.
Serves 2.

title: ole fashioned raccoon
directions: Cut raccoon into serving size pieces, being sure to remove all kernels (located underneath each leg under the skin).
Place in a large pot of water and boil until tender.
Remove from water and place in roaster pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, sage and about 1 cup of broth in which the "coon" was cooked.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes with the roaster lid on.
Then remove the lid and pour catsup and small amount of hot sauce on each piece (both sides).
Bake an additional 15 or 20 minutes, uncovered.
Serve hot.

title: hearty baked macaroni(health conscious)
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato puree, water, Italian seasonings and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
In another bowl, combine cottage cheese, onion powder and the remaining garlic powder.
Spray with vegetable cooking spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.

Spoon 1/3 of the tomato mixture in the dish. Layer 1/2 of the macaroni, all of the cheese mixture, 1/3 of the tomato mixture, the remaining 1/2 of the macaroni, then the remaining 1/3 of the tomato mixture.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Let stand before serving.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over ice ring of cranberry juice in punch bowl.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and heat 1 cup of juice.
Add gelatin.
Beat the cheese into warm mixture.
Fold in fruit and chill until syrupy. Fold in nuts, sweetener, topping mix and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: home fries
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet. Add potatoes in a single layer. Sprinkle with onions, salt, paprika and pepper. Cover and cook over medium-low heat 10 to 12 minutes, stirring once or twice, until potatoes are almost tender.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle with topping.

title: berry's barbecue ribs
directions: In a large bowl, combine catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce, hickory flavored salt, pepper and garlic.
Cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes or refrigerate for up to 5 days.
Arrange hot coals around a drip pan. Place ribs, fat side up, on grill rack over drip pan (not over coals).
Grill 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is very tender.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf(delicious)
directions: Mix together first 7 items.
Heat brown sugar, vinegar and tomato paste until blended.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into the meat ingredients.
Form into loaf pan.
Frost meat loaf with remaining tomato sauce.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 6 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and set aside. Mix 2 cups sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice.
Put half of batter in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Add half of apple mixture, then remaining batter and top with apples.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ohio valley pioneer taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream with taco seasoning in a bowl; mix well.
Spread evenly on serving platter.
Layer all other ingredients over the mixture.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: honey apple barbecue sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine barbecue sauce, honey, jelly, catsup, water, celery, sugar, relish, mustard and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat; cool.
Store in bottle in refrigerator.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, eggs and 2 tablespoons of vanilla.
Beat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Fill 24 cupcake papers.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and cool 5 minutes. Centers will drop.
Blend in separate bowl the sour cream, 1 tablespoon vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar.
Fill centers with mixture. Top with spoonful cherry pie filling.
Bake 5 more minutes at 300°.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Add hot water (or sherry) to raisins and set aside to cool.
In large bowl, with electric mixer set to medium-high, beat together shortening, sugar and molasses until light and fluffy.
Set mixer at low speed and beat in eggs and pumpkin.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Toss chopped nuts in flour mixture. Gradually beat flour-nut mixture into creamed mixture.
Add raisins and water (or sherry).
Mix until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Allow to cool on racks before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lasagne
directions: Bring water to boil in large pot.
Cook according to box directions.
When done, transfer cooked noodles to large bowl of ice water.
While noodles are cooking, cook ground beef until done.
Drain off fat.
Cook sausage (remove skin) until done and crumbly.
Open mushroom can and drain.
Open fried sweet peppers and drain.
Mix Ricotta with 1 egg.

title: mock pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack into jars, seal and process for 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.
This is good in anything that calls for crushed pineapple.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix ground beef, Veg-All (drained) and soup.
Place in microwave for 2 minutes.
Place 1 pie crust in pie dish or pan and brown lightly in oven.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Place crust on top.
Cook as directed on box.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pot.
Stir in onions, pepper and garlic.
Cook until done.
Stir in flour.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, salt, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and okra.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add crabmeat, shrimp and fish.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix ingredients; chill before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: party lime punch(30 servings)
directions: For years I have browsed the fresh food sections of grocery stores and farmer's markets, seizing anything new.
My family has indulged my whims and together we have discovered many new treats.

title: fried pies
directions: Place apples in cold water in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then reduce to medium to low heat.
Simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add sugar, honey, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cool. Make biscuit dough.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 6-inch rounds.
Place 2 tablespoons apples in center of each round.

title: wicky wacky cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together in the pan you plan to bake in (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Add water, vanilla and 5 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake in this same pan at 350°.
Do not grease pan. Bake about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp in herb sauce
directions: Place shrimp in shallow dish.
Combine onions, oil, vinegar, thyme, marjoram, bay leaf and cayenne pepper.
Pour over shrimp. Marinate 1 to 2 hours.
Remove shrimp from marinade, reserving marinade.
Place shrimp on an oiled baking pan, flesh side up. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes.
Return shrimp to marinade and chill several hours.
Or, may be served hot immediately after cooking.
Serves 8.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Drain all liquid from vegetables and place all ingredients in a large saucepan or pot and cook until vegetables are tender (usually about 30 minutes on medium heat).

title: puffy apple oven pancake
