directions: Grease a 9 inch pie plate with 2 T. of melted butter.
Evenly sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on melted butter.
Arrange the apple slices uniformly in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients just until moistened and pour over apple mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.
Invert on a dinner plate and serve hot with your favorite syrup.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix in a large iron skillet the dates and oleo. Beat eggs and sugar well. Add to date mixture and cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Make small balls and roll in coconut with buttered hands.

title: carrot bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.	Mix
eggs and oil, then mix with dry ingredients.
Fold
in
carrots,
chopped walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 350°
for
55 minutes in lightly greased and floured pan.

title: my sis' favorite cake
directions: Mix dates, nuts and cherries with flour and sugar.
Beat eggs until creamy, add vanilla.
Stir into mixture.
Turn into
9 x 4 greased waxed pan.
Bake 300° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: no bake banana peanut nuggets
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Flatten slightly.
Roll edge in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: southern style macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine cheese, macaroni, margarine and seasonings.
Mix well. Spoon macaroni mixture into greased 8-inch square baking dish. Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Serves 4 to 6.

title: low-fat double use barbecued pot roast(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in olive oil.
Add water, tomato sauce, sliced onion and crushed garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry dessert salad
directions: Dissolve
gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries.
Stir occasionally
until
thawed.
Fold
in
undrained	pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
Spoon sour cream over gelatin.
Pour on remaining gelatin.	Refrigerate until set.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour in pie shell.

title: chicken cutlets of life
directions: Pound chicken breasts.
Mix milk, egg, garlic and pepper.
Add chicken cutlets.
Marinate at least 1 hour.
Mix fresh crumbs, seasoned salt and parsley.
Dip marinated cutlets in crumb mixture. Fry in hot oil until golden brown for about 5 to 7 minutes each side.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together in large container.
Store in jars.

title: four layer pie
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. In a small bowl, mix the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in melted margarine until well combined.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining crumbs gently into pan and bake for 12 to 15 minutes. With electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes longer until set.
When cool, cut into 2-inch squares and then cut diagonally in half.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms 3 minutes in butter; add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.

title: strufoli
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Add eggs, vanilla, sugar and orange peel.
Stir.
Knead dough until soft.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll small sections of dough into strips and cut in 1/2-inch pieces. Fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain.
Glaze with honey and sprinkles.

title: sunbeam waffle
directions: Using electric mixer, beat egg yolks 1 minute.
Add milk and beat 1 minute longer.
Add sifted dry ingredients at low speed and beat 1 minute.
Add the melted butter and beat until blended.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Use 1 1/2 cups of batter to fill grids once.
Pour batter in center and spread evenly to fill all 4 corners.
Makes three 4 section waffles.

title: scalloped rice(makes 6 servings)
directions: Mix cooked rice, flour, salt, green onions and parsley.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Pour light cream over mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs, saving the whites for the meringue. Mix flour, cocoa and sugar in saucepan. Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. When thick, remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter, stirring well.
Pour into baked pie shell. (I use Pet deep dish frozen crust.) Beat the egg whites until they begin to get stiff.

Add a dash of cream of tartar and a dash of salt. Slowly add 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar, beating until egg whites form stiff peaks. Put meringue on pie and bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Melt butter.
Blend flour and pepper.
Cook on low heat until bubbly.
Stir in broth and milk bringing to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in salmon, onions and parsley thoroughly and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: salt and cholesterol-free pie crust
directions: In medium bowl, cut margarine into flour until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Stir in cold water until mixture holds together. Shape into ball.
On floured surface, roll dough into 11-inch circle and put into pie pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° until done (or lightly browned).

title: layered ranchero dip(mexican dip)
directions: On a 15 x 10-inch or large shallow pan or serving platter, thinly spread bean dip.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Mix good; pour over bean dip.
Sprinkle with chillies, cheese, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Serve with chips.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Grease (or lightly spray with cooking spray) bottom only of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2 inches. Beat cake mix, water, oil and eggs in large bowl on low speed 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly (do not overbeat), or stir 2 minutes by hand.
Pour half of the batter into pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: helen rose's ambrosia
directions: Peel the oranges, using Florida navels if possible, into a large bowl.
This means using a paring knife and peeling like a potato.
Slice small pieces off each one until you get to the "core," and squeeze the juice out and discard the core.
Add the can of fruit cocktail, pineapple chunks and coconut.
Mix all this together and refrigerate; it blends best in about 24 hours.
As you begin to mix the ingredients, note the quantity of each as it is added; adjust this by adding less or more.
There is no fixed ratio that must be used, only what you think looks good.
A friend of ours is allergic to coconut, so when we fix this for a crowd which includes her, we leave out the coconut until we reserve a big bowlful for her, then mix the coconut with the rest.
We have found that the canned coconut rather than the packaged dry works better for us.
Experiment!
There is no way you can go wrong on this for Thanksgiving and Christmas.
Note there is no added sugar.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Stir softened cream cheese into the whipped topping. Gradually add cherry pie filling, blending well.
Fold drained mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks into cherry mixture.
Pour into 8-cup mold and freeze overnight or until firm. Unmold and serve.

title: orange slice christmas cake
directions: Sift together flour and salt; set aside.
Combine candy, dates, nuts and coconut with 1/2 cup of flour mixture; set aside. Cream together the butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Combine the buttermilk and soda.
Add alternately with the flour mixture to butter and eggs.
Mix well and add fruit mixture.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Remove from oven while cake is still hot.
Pour a combination of 2 cups powdered sugar and 1 cup orange juice (canned not frozen) over cake.
Let cool, then refrigerate overnight before removing from pan.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour; add salt and ice water slowly until ball of dough forms.
Roll out for double crust.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and margarine to soft ball stage. Allow mixture to cool, then add the milk.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Wash apples.
Peel, quarter, and remove core and slice.
Heat apple juice in saucepan.
Add apple slices; cover and simmer. Stir in cornstarch which has been blended with a little water. Fill pastry shell with apples.
Dot margarine over top.
Top with remaining pastry.
Trim edges and cut vents in top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: country smoked roaster
directions: Remove and discard giblets from roaster.
Rub skin and cavity with oil and season with chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
If using gas grill, open all vents and prepare coals at least 30 minutes before grilling.
When coals are medium and covered with grey ash, place drip pan at center in bottom of grill.
Arrange 25 to 30 hot coals at either end of pan.
Place roaster on grill over drip pan, breast side up.
Cover grill and smoke bird about two hours.
Begin checking after 1 1/2 hours.

title: petite cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until fluffy.
Put paper cups in muffin pan.
Place vanilla wafer in each cup, rounded side down.
Fill 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling.
Chill.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, butter, salt, pepper, onion and caraway seed with enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk; heat but do not boil.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together several times the first 5 ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Cut the vegetable shortening into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and water/yeast mixture.
Work together until all flour is moistened.
Cover and refrigerate. Use as needed.
Will keep for a week or longer.

title: irish potato pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes at 400°.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and milk; beat well.
Stir in potatoes and vanilla. Pour into pie shell; sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli - rice - cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° until broccoli is tender.

title: mushroom chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, mix rice, soups and water.
Place chicken on top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: smoked trout spread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, flake fish.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and cayenne pepper; mix well.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheezy cream of chicken and broccoli soup
directions: Cook chicken in 1 1/2 cups water; add chicken base (can be bought at Sam's Wholesale Club), and cook until well done.
Cool and debone.
Add all other ingredients, except Cheez Whiz and milk.
Cook 15 minutes on medium.
Reduce heat to low and simmer another 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, to be sure that it is not sticking to the pot.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: potato soup
directions: Pour water in very large pot.
Add diced potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Do Not Drain - leave water with potatoes.
Add the soup and stir well.
In a separate pan, melt butter and add chicken boulion and flour.
When it becomes a paste consistency, pour this into pot with potatoes.
Add the half and half stirring well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8 - 12 people.

title: carolyn's quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into muffin pan.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients with salad dressing and Salad Supreme.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add bell pepper and onion and cook until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce, salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt and serve with garlic bread.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together like pie dough.
Divide into 8 parts.
Pare, core and cut apples into quarters.
Place apple pieces on individual rolled dough sections.
Sprinkle apples with butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Fold dough upward around apples.
Place in deep dish pan.
Boil the remaining 6 ingredients in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: steak with tomato sauce
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper to taste.
Coat meat with flour.
Heat oil in skillet; add meat and brown well on both sides. Add onion rings during last of browning.
(If you like, take steak out of pan and drain on paper towels to absorb some of grease while sauteing onion rings.)
Layer in greased casserole meat, then onions; top with mushrooms and pour tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water on top.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for two hours.

title: trout amandine
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Bone trout, if desired.
Season. Combine egg and cream or milk.
Dip fish in flour, then in egg-cream mixture and again in flour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake croissants on cookie sheet, laying one next to the other, to form bottom crust.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, dressing or mayo and Ranch mix.
Put on top of crust.
Cover with fresh vegetables (carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, purple cabbage, onions, etc.) and cheese (optional). Refrigerate overnight.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat water, vinegar, salt and turmeric and boil until they turn color.
For more dill flavor, put dill weed or dill seed in each jar.
Put in jars, covering with juice and seal.

title: casey's luscious lemon pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust, reserving 1/3 cup crumbs. Chill.
Whip the cream until soft peaks form.
Slowly add thawed concentrate, sweetened condensed milk and food color, mixing well. (Do not overbeat).
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with crumbs. I thinly slice a clean lemon, half the slices and put facing the same direction denoting each piece.
It looks pretty and is easy to cut even pieces.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eating wells chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium-sized bowl stir together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat.
Cook, swirling the pan, until the butter turns nutty brown, 30 to 60 seconds.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until smooth. Add egg, egg white and vanilla; beat until well incorporated.
Add the reserved flour mixture and chocolate chips and stir with a wooden spoon just until combined.
(The batter will be runny.) Drop the batter by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto the prepared baking sheets.
Bake, one sheet at a time, for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Transfer the cookies to racks and let cool.
Calories 63, fat 2g.

title: oven fried zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Combine water and oil in a small bowl.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper in a paper or plastic bag.
Stir zucchini slices a few at a time, in oil-water mixture; then shake up in crumb mixture. Arrange slices in a single layer in a shallow nonstick pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, uncovered, without turning, until slices are brown and tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except morsels and mix well.
Fold in morsels.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Combine oats, vanilla and nuts in large bowl.
Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour cocoa mix into oats and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: pennsylvania dutch bread
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; let cool, then add the yeast which has been dissolved in warm water.
Stir in molasses.
Beat vigorously.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead for several minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl and allow to rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again until doubled.
Punch down and form into 3 medium loaves.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar, and vanilla in large bowl.
Add eggs, using wooden spoon; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend in egg mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Sprinkle chopped nuts in bottom of pan. Mix rest of ingredients. Pour in pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Cover potatoes with cold water for several hours. Remove 1/4 cup of potato water.
Grate potatoes; add with remaining ingredients to 1/4 cup potato water.
Bake in small cakes on a greased griddle.
Turn and brown on both sides.

title: delicious cobbler
directions: *To keep fruit from turning brown, squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon onto fruit.

title: barbecue venison
directions: Soak meat overnight in salt water (1 tablespoon salt and just enough water to cover).
Put all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook at low for about 10 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles or as sandwiches.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup reserved juice and cornstarch.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Beat Cool Whip and softened cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until well blended.
Blend in lemon juice and vanilla.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer. Grease and flour large tube baking pan. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 45 minutes, about 3 inches from bottom burner.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into frozen pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: three day refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 2 layers.
Cool layers and split.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut.
(Reserve some coconut to sprinkle on finished cake.)
Chill sour cream mixture; reserve 1 cup for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers and on top of cake.
Mix reserved cup and Cool Whip.
Spread on top and sides.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Store in airtight container for 3 days in refrigerator.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Heat until hot.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix per instructions on box.
Cook and take out of oven.
Pierce holes in cake with fork.
Pour pineapple and juice on cake.
Spread evenly.
Put Cool Whip on cake when ready to serve.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Cook macaroni according to instructions; drain.
Into a baking dish, layer mixture and cheese until it's all used.
(Reserve some cheese for top.)
Mix soup and pour over mixture, then top with cheese.
Bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients, add to cream mixture.
Add peanuts, then corn flakes. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, oil and margarine; add beaten egg and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in cereals and chips.
Roll dough into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Slightly flatten each with sugared glass.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Bring Jell-O and pineapple to boiling.
Let cool.
Mix buttermilk with Cool Whip; mix with Jell-O and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate until set.

title: jerky marinade and preparation instructions
directions: Mix all ingredients listed in a large bowl.
Cut approximately 3 pounds of lean meat in strips 1/16 to 1/8-inch thick, 1 to 3-inches long and 1/2 to 1-inch wide.
Best to cut the meat diagonal to the grain.
(Note: For best results, freeze meat on a flat surface first, then slice after it starts to thaw.)
Add meat to marinade so that marinade covers all meat.
Cover bowl and set in refrigerator.
Stir meat and marinade once a day for 3 to 5 days.
To dry, place meat on rack or skewer it and place in an oven set to 100° to 200°.
Prop oven door open about 1-inch.
Start checking meat after about 2 1/2 hours.
Most meat will be done by 4 1/2 hours.

title: egg salad deluxe
directions: Soften gelatin in 3/4 cup consomme.
Heat remaining consomme and dissolve gelatin in it.
Refrigerate until partially set. Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fill mold and refrigerate until set.
Unmold onto lettuce-lined plate.
Garnish with swirls of salad dressing. Serves 6.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Clean and tear up spinach and put into serving dish.
Add bacon pieces and eggs.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease bottoms of two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar, salt, bananas, shortening and eggs.
Blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: baked crabmeat spread
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add red pepper, onions and garlic; cook until vegetables are tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk; cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Remove from heat; fold in crabmeat.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned and cheese is melted.
Serve with Melba toast rounds.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Don't overmix.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Put in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cut in squares while still warm.
Good without nuts.

title: gratin of cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling, salted water for about 12 minutes. Drain and puree or mash. Blend in milk, butter and mustard. Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper. Place in a shallow baking dish and cover with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until a golden crust has formed over the top.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, mix 5 minutes apart each ingredient (flour and butter), then add flavor.
Mix everything for about 30 minutes.
Bake on 350°.

title: oreo mud
directions: Place thin layer of crushed Oreos on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix the sugar, pudding, milk and cream cheese together and layer this mixture over Oreos.
Continue to layer Oreos and mixture, ending with Oreos.
Top with whipped topping.

title: presto primavera
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions; drain. Heat the vegetables, tomatoes and chicken (or ham) in a large saucepan while pasta is cooking. Mix in the pasta and heat thoroughly. Season to taste and cook for 15 minutes. Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: easy chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large microwavable bowl, mix corn syrup, sugar, chocolate chips and butter.
Microwave approximately 1 minute on Medium heat, just so chocolate chips are soft.
Stir just until mixed. Let cool to room temperature.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mary's blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into muffin pans lined with papers or lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, eggs, cornmeal, syrup and milk; mix all together.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: conway's pickled beets
directions: Drain liquid from one can of beets and discard.
Take one can of liquid and add sugar and cider vinegar.
Bring to boil and put beets in.
Bring to another boil and turn off heat.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Put in quart jars and seal.
Let stand 24 hours, then refrigerate.

title: fried shrimp
directions: De-head, peel and devein shrimp.
Rinse and drain well. Place 2 c. butter milk in bowl.
Put 2 c. flour on wax paper.
Let shrimp soak in milk for 20 minutes.
Dip in flour and then deep fry until golden brown.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: On wax paper, combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken. In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Push chicken to one side.
Stir in soup and water, stirring to loosen brown bits.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until well blended; add topping.

title: magic nanaimo bars
directions: Lightly grease 9-inch square pan.
Melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine; stir in sugar and cocoa.
Remove from heat; add egg and vanilla.
Stir in cracker crumbs, coconut and walnuts.
Press into pan.
Cream 1/4 cup butter, milk, custard powder and powdered sugar.
Spread over bottom layer.
Put into freezer for 7 minutes. Melt semi-sweet chocolate.
Remove bars from freezer and drizzle chocolate over top.
Cut into small squares.

title: butterfingers
directions: Mix powdered sugar, Rice Krispies, peanut butter and margarine together and form into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips, Hershey bar and paraffin.
Dip peanut butter ball in chocolate mixture with toothpick.
Cool.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place 1-inch balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done (20 minutes).

title: hot venison chili
directions: Brown venison in hot oil in a Dutch oven, stirring until it crumbles.
Stir in onion, celery and garlic; cook until tender. Add water and next 8 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and cook 30 minutes.

title: honey roasted red potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Lightly coat an 11 x 7-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Lay potatoes in a single layer in prepared dish.
Combine the melted butter, honey, mustard, salt and pepper; drizzle over potatoes.
Bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook the meat and onion until done. Salt and pepper. Add the chili. Add the water.
Simmer for a few minutes. Take the tortilla shells and dip in hot grease and take right out.
Take the enchilada sauce and tomato sauce and mix in a bowl together.
Dip tortillas in sauce and fill with meat mixture.
Put in grated cheese and roll up individually in pan.
Hold together with toothpick.
Pour remainder of enchilada sauce and meat mixture over top after they are in the pan. Garnish with grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and sauce bubbles.
Add lettuce on top.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage for 3 minutes; drain.
Layer 1/2 cabbage, 1/2 soup and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vanilla icing
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat together sugar, milk, corn syrup, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Drizzle over bread.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In glass measuring cup melt butter in microwave.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Stir to coat.
Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes, until onion is soft.
Into vegetable mixture stir flour until blended.
Cook on High 1 minute, stirring halfway through cooking.
Gradually stir in broth and milk until smooth.
Cook sauce on High 4 to 6 minutes, until thick, stirring twice.
To sauce add chicken and pimento.
Cook on High 3 minutes.
In a small bowl with whisk beat egg yolks.
Stir 1/4 cup sauce from chicken into beaten egg yolks.
Pour egg yolk mixture back into remaining chicken mixture, beating rapidly to prevent lumping.
If you like, stir in sherry in chicken mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon chicken and sauce into warmed patty shells.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add all other ingredients and beat well. Bake at 375°.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread.
Roll or pat into rectangle.
Spread on sausage and onions.
Sprinkle on caraway seed.
Roll in jelly roll fashion.
Continue with directions on bread dough package (350° for 30 minutes).
Brush with melted margarine after removal from oven.
Let cool before cutting, if you can.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain well, then add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour. If you double recipe, cut down on half the vinegar.

title: enchiladas conquesa
directions: Brown meat; stir in remaining ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place rounded tablespoonfuls of meat sauce and cheese in each tortilla; roll up tightly.
Place seam side down in a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Place peaches in bottom of unbaked pastry shell.
Mix sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Fill pie shell with heavy cream.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: soy pork chops
directions: Mix lemon juice with soy sauce.
Place pork chops in pan; cover with soy mixture.
Let set 30 minutes.
(Iron skillet is good.)
Cover and cook in 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Take out and put about 1/3 cup of water in.
Cover and let cook about 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: millionaire pie - baked pie shell
directions: Cream sugar with the cream cheese.
Add drained pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Place in pie shell. Refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: tri-baked beans
directions: Brown bacon.
Save small amount of drippings.
Add onion and garlic; brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a covered dish at 350° for 1 hour or longer.
Also good to cook in crock-pot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Let cool.
Grease pan and tear chicken into pieces and place in pan.
Lightly sprinkle with pepper.
In a mixing bowl combine soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup of water.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter.
Crush crackers.
Pour butter over cracker crumbs.
Cover casserole with crumb mixture. Cook at 300 degree or 325 degree for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in well greased tube or Bundt pan 2 - 3 hours at 300 degrees.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs.
Beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: About 45 minutes before serving: On cutting board, cut each chicken breast in half.
Working with 1/2 at a time, place it skin side up.
With tip of sharp knife, starting parallel and close to large end, cut meat away from bone.
Discard bones and skin chicken.
Slice breast into 1/8-inch thick pieces.
In medium bowl, mix sliced chicken, soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch; set aside.
Cook linguine according to package and drain.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix well and bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil wrap.
Must have a lip around it. Line with graham crackers.
Place a pecan half on each square of graham cracker.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of the sauce, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg. In a 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough.
Cut potatoes in slices, but not all the way through.
(Lay a wooden spoon handle beside potato to bump and not cut through.)
Place in dish.
Sprinkle with melted margarine and parsley, chives or sage.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir together dry ingredients; set aside.
In small bowl, mix egg, banana, milk and oil.
Add liquid mixture all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: peaches in orange liqueur
directions: Wash, halve and pit peaches.
Arrange cut side down, one layer deep, in shallow baking pan.
Cream together butter and sugar; stir in orange liqueur and lemon juice.
Spoon mixture over peaches and refrigerate, if desired.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion. Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: velvet smooth creme pie(basic filling)
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt. Add 1 cup milk. Mix smooth. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring briskly. Continue to stir and let boil until smoothly thickened, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat. With fork, beat eggs or egg yolks with remaining 1 cup milk. Gradually stir into hot mixture, then put back over heat. Bring to a boil, stirring, and boil until mixture thickens a bit more, about 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in butter and vanilla. Top with meringue or chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Turn into baked crust.
Whip 1/2 cup cream very stiff.
Fold in 1/4 cup mayonnaise.
Spread over salad in pie shell, leaving 1-inch of salad around edge, uncovered.
Place in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Layer in order: lettuce, carrot, onion and peas.
Cover with mayonnaise and sour cream mixed.
Cook bacon and serve over salad the next day after tossing.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Brown crumbs in 1/2 stick butter.
Melt remaining half of butter in small pan over low heat.
Stir in flour to make a smooth mixture.
Gradually add about 1/2 cup milk.
Add other ingredients; cook slowly, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Add water 2 inches above beans. Add salt pork; cover and simmer until beans are done.
Add next 10 ingredients; cover and cook 1 hour.
Cut sausage in 1/4-inch slices.
Brown and add to beans.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: jalapeno meat rotel dip
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Put all ingredients into a crock-pot and cook.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together flour and powdered sugar.
Add margarine.
Blend together well and press with fingers into a 9-inch pie pan (bottom and sides).
Bake at 350°
for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool at room temperature.

title: three layer cookies
directions: Combine
margarine,
sugar,
egg
and
cocoa.
Melt
in double boiler or heavy pan and heat until slightly thick.	Add to mixture:
crushed
graham crackers, coconut and nuts.
Mix and pat in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: cheese dinner muffins
directions: Mix together Bisquick, egg, buttermilk and cheese. Add enough ice water to make a very soft batter. Spoon into lightly greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until well risen and golden brown.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Cook pie shell in 350° oven until golden brown.
Cook milk, sugar, flour, cocoa, vanilla and egg yolks on top of stove until thick.
Put in pie shell.
Mix egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar; blend until fluffy.
Brown lightly in oven.

title: hickory brisket slices
directions: Place brisket on grill of barbecue smoker, away from hot coals.
Salt.
Add dampened hickory to coals; close smoker hood. Slowly hickory-barbecue 4 hours or until tender.

title: stella's chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in broth.
Cool and cut into fairly large pieces. Peel and dice apples.
Cut grapes in half.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve as main dish for luncheon.

title: kentucky transparent pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp andouille chowder
directions: In a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven, heat butter over medium-high heat. Add sausage and saut, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 minutes until sausage is browned. Stir in onion, celery, carrot and garlic; reduce heat to medium-low. Cover pot and cook for 4 to 5 minutes until onion and other vegetables are softened.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese, keep warm.
Brown meat and keep warm. Cook chopped broccoli.
Fry the cubed potatoes, keep warm.
Saute onions.
In glasg baking dish spread meat on bottom.
Cover that with macaroni and cheese.
Spread broccoli, potatoes and cheese on top.
Sprinkle on onions.
Put in oven at 400° to heat.
When hot, cover with grated cheese and return to oven until melted.
Then eat.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Rinse kraut with cold water.
Press to drain well.
Combine onion, soup, milk and mustard in bowl.
Blend well.
Spread kraut in 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until noodles are tender.

title: rainy saturday mexican holiday
directions: Combine barbecue sauce and water in skillet.
Mix tuna, pepper and onion together; add to sauce.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes. Add margarine to warm rice, then add cheese; mix well.
Serve tuna mixture over rice.

title: mini meat loaf
directions: Mix six loaves and brown on both sides.
Drain off fat.
Add rest of soup and 2 tablespoons water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: garlic vinegar(extra strong)
directions: Put in a jar with a tight lid.
Let stand one week or more before using.

title: homemade granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl combine oats, nuts, raisins, sunflower seeds and nonfat dry milk.
Mix completely. Add melted butter and honey.
Mix to coat.
Place granola mixture on two cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoon into hot grease. Cook until golden brown on both sides. You can substitute 2 cans of tuna for the salmon to make this recipe.

title: rainbow confetti cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In large mixer bowl, cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Press about 15 morsels in top of dough. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 11 minutes or until light brown.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain; rinse with hot water.
In 2 tablespoons shortening, brown beef, stirring with fork.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and green onions.
Mix well.
Add cooked noodles; mix lightly.
Place half of noodles in a well-greased casserole. Cover with 1/2 of meat; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mother's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas to a pulp and add soda, mixing thoroughly.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add to bananas, then add eggs, then add flour, salt and vanilla and mix well.
Bake about 1 hour in loaf pan in 300° oven.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and shape into balls, any size.
Put on cookie sheet pan with sides and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out and drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Add sauce (catsup, vinegar, salt, sugar, pepper and Worcestershire sauce).
Pour over meatballs in casserole dish and bake 1/2 hour at 350° with the lid on.

title: mexican tuna salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tuna, red pepper, corn and green onions in a bowl.
Combine salsa, sour cream and cumin in a small bowl.
Gently stir salsa mixture into tuna.

title: brie torte
directions: Chop apricots and soak overnight in brandy.
Blend butter and cream cheese in mixer.
Fold in apricots and walnuts.
Cut Brie hamburger-style.
Remove rind off top and sides; leave on bottom. Spread mixture on bottom half and place top of Brie on filling. Coat top and sides with remaining mixture.
Garnish with 2 apricot halves and 2 walnut halves.
This will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: cool whip crazy cakes (berry funny faces)
directions: Additional Garnish Suggestions: blueberries, string licorice, toasted coconut, sprinkles and assorted candies.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients into a ball.
Roll in chopped parsley. Refrigerate before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Use two packages noodle seasoning with 3 packages noodles. Saute onions in margarine; add water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil and stir in broken noodles.
Cook, uncovered, 3 minutes. Stir in broccoli and garlic salt.
Simmer 4 minutes and add milk and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
It is ready when cheese melts.
Very, very good!

title: brownies
directions: Let butter stand until soft.
Blend butter and sugar together. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and cocoa.
Stir until mixed well.
Add sifted flour.
Stir with spoon until all ingredients are well blended.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in two 8-inch square pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients (except sesame seed); form into balls.
Roll in sesame seed.
Eat.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans well.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: marshmallow crispy treats
directions: Melt margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: french onion soup
directions: Mix onions and margarine in skillet. Cover and cook until soft and light brown. Mix next 5 ingredients together and add to onions. Add broth. Cover and cook until onions are very tender. Place slice of bread on bottom. Put soup in. Add Provolone cheese on top. Place under broiler until melted.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well. Add one grated hard-boiled egg to mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with sliced egg and biscuits.
Cook until bubbly at 350°.

title: linguine with shrimp sauce
directions: Cook linguine 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Brown shrimp, garlic and parsley in oil over gentle fire 10 minutes.
Remove shrimp. Add salt, pepper, tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer 1 hour. Add shrimp, oregano and basil and cook 5 minutes.
Pour shrimp sauce over linguine.
Don't cook shrimp too long in tomato.
Brown first; put in last.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Beat margarine and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugars.
Cream thoroughly before adding egg.
Beat some more.
Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder; beat into creamed mixture.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Make into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and press chocolate kiss in center of each.
Place 2 inches apart on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. Mix soup, sour cream, beaten eggs and milk.
In a casserole
dish, put a layer of onions, cover with soup mixture. Then sprinkle with grated cheese.
Another layer of onions, etc. Top with crushed Saltines. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato layer cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat oil and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add sweet potato, water and

vanilla; mix well. In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, fold into the sweet potato mixture. Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; add to potato mixture. Stir in pecans. Pour into three greased 9 inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 22-27 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing to wire racks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange together, add sugar.
Let stand a little while.
Add fruits and nuts.
Add to Jell-O and chill.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Cut off 1/2 inch of top or bottom of peeled onions.
Place in boiling water for about 7 minutes.
Remove onion centers and set aside to use in stuffing.
Fry sausage until red disappears; drain.
Chop onion centers.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley, sugar, cinnamon, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff onion shells.
Stand shells up in buttered baking dish.
May top with small pieces of bacon and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Hamburger may be substituted or ground turkey or chicken.

title: cottage cheese orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges (drained).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Mix with lemon juice.
Layer the ingredients in order.
Serve with nachos.

title: shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grind walnuts into a coarse meal. Cream butter and sugar.
Blend with walnuts.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon dough onto lightly greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Smooth out to fill pan evenly.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes 75 bars (1 x 2-inches).

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Layer in pan, kidney beans, pork and beans and lima beans.
Layer 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup regular sugar and 1 cup catsup.
Layer bacon on top.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cook for 15 minutes, then stir every 15 minutes.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: cabbage roll paprikash
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling water for 6 minutes.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mushrooms, garlic, salt and thyme.
Stir in egg.
Place a half cup of chicken mixture in the center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold sides of the cabbage leaf towards center, over the filling, and then fold and overlap ends to make a small bundle.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: cinnamon christmas ornaments
directions: Mix applesauce with cinnamon to form a stiff dough. Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutter.
Make a hole for ribbon.
Put on rack to dry.
Let air dry several days, turning occasionally.

title: marshmallow rocky road fudge
directions: Sprinkle walnuts evenly over the bottom of a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Set aside. Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it
combine sugar, milk and salt.
Heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil 2 minutes (222°), stirring frequently to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat; immediately stir in chocolate and vanilla. Beat until chocolate is melted and blended.
Cover walnuts with half of the fudge mixture. Top with marshmallows, pressing them gently into the fudge; spread with remaining fudge.

title: raspberry cheese cake
directions: Mix 1 box of Danish dessert as directed on box, using juice from raspberries as part of the water.
Cool, but don't let set up.
Mix together flour, brown sugar, margarine and nuts.
Press into bottom of dripper pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and then crumble until fine.
Press 1/2 or 3/4 of it back into pan for the bottom.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together. Mix Dream Whip as directed on the package and then add to cheese mixture.
Put on top of crumbs in pan; add Danish dessert mixture on top of this.
Add rest of crumbs on top.
Put in the fridge overnight or let set for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter sandwich supreme
directions: Take one 1 tablespoon peanut butter.
Put into a small bowl. Take maple syrup or honey and mix it in with the peanut butter and stir.
Then spread it on a slice of bread.
Sprinkle it with the raisins.
Take your banana, slice it up and lay over the raisins. Put on your other slice of bread.
It is ready to eat.
Praise the Lord!!

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together at high speed until mixture looks like ice cream.
Throughly beat in eggs, one at a time.
Put buttermilk and soda in 1-pint measure cup and mix together.
By hand, stir in the flour in several additions into the cream mixture.
Alternate with buttermilk mixture and mix only until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door during first hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Pan-fry sausage.
Drain.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Beat remainder together.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cool peach pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients with a hand mixer at low speed until blended.
Fold in peaches by hand.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch buttered pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork lo mein(for a crowd!)
directions: Marinate pork, soy sauce, wine and ginger. Saute celery, onions and mushrooms.
Remove from pan.
Add pork to pan and brown.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Excellent fresh vegetable dip or cracker dip.

title: world's easiest cobbler
directions: Melt butter/margarine in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and stir into melted butter/margarine.
Pour sweetened fruit over batter and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In bottom of casserole dish put 1/2 of cornbread stuffing mix. Debone chicken; put on top of stuffing mix.
Mix together the chicken and celery soup with 1 1/2 cups broth from chicken.
Pour over other ingredients.
Put remaining stuffing mix on top and dot with butter.
Bake in 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Stir to prevent sticking. Pour over Rice Krispies. Spoon on wax paper.
Then shape in balls.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffed tuna shells
directions: Cook and drain pasta shells as directed on package; pat dry. Rinse frozen peas with cold water to separate; drain and pat dry. Mix yogurt and mayonnaise in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Gently fold in peas.
Spoon 1 heaping tablespoon tuna mixture into each shell.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: chocolate zucchini muffins
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar very well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Add zucchini. Line muffin tins with paper cups and fill 2/3 full.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of muffins before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: fat-free meat loaf
directions: Crush crackers until meat holds together.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into a loaf.
Place in meat loaf pan.
If your heart desires, add ketchup to the top.
Cook at 400° for 55 minutes.
It's yummy!
Eat as much as you wish.
You won't get fat!

title: collard greens with neckbones
directions: Parboil neckbones in large saucepan.
Remove from broth.
Add greens and cook on low heat until tender.
Add bacon drippings and red pepper sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from stove eye and add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Pour mixture over Rice Krispies and mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.

title: pecan bread
directions: Mix in a bowl the whole-wheat flour, pastry or cake flour, brown sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add buttermilk and pecan meats. Stir well. Spoon into a buttered loaf pan, 9 x 5-inches. Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread pieces in bottom of greased 13 x 8 x 2-inch casserole. Spread browned sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix together beaten eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and add about 5 ounces crushed Doritos and mix. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Then cover with shredded cheese.

title: cheese cake(this recipe makes 2 pies!)
directions: Mix and pour into crust.
Add any topping (cherries, nuts, blueberries, etc.).

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Prepare lasagne.
Steam spinach until defrosted, then drain. Add Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese and nutmeg.
Mix well and set aside.

title: chow mein
directions: Mix all together and bake 2 hours in slow oven.
Last half hour, generously cover with chow mein noodles.
Serve with soy sauce (can add mushrooms).
We like to serve this with chopped fresh tomatoes and fresh chopped green pepper.
Also very good with cashews sprinkled over top.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Mix with other ingredients with just enough mayonnaise to mix well.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt, then add shortening, milk and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart Pyrex bowl. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 4 more minutes. Add butter and vanilla; microwave 1 more minute.
Take out and add soda; stir quickly and pour on greased foil.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix in cocoa, flour, walnuts and coconut flakes.
Mix and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Quickly spread marshmallow cream.
Let cool.

title: tuna on a shoestring
directions: Blend and chill.
Can serve on a bed of lettuce or plain.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Combine all vegetables and stir until hot.
Add soy sauce and sauce mix.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook white rice for 10 minutes on medium heat and serve vegetables over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Put into measuring cup shortening; fill to 3/4 cup with boiling water.
Add the orange rind and juice and egg.
Cool slightly; add the liquid to dry ingredients.
Mix as for muffins and add cranberries and nuts. Grease and flour Number 303 cans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: layered pasta ricotta pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Break pasta into thirds and cook; drain. In skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender; remove from heat.
Add vermicelli, 1/2 cup Romano cheese and 1 egg.
Mix well. Press into well greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine 2 eggs, Ricotta cheese, spinach, salt and 1/2 cup Romano cheese.
Spread over pasta.

title: granola
directions: Mix well. Spread on a cookie sheet and bake at 250° to 300° about 40
minutes.
(Use other dried fruit: cranberries, prunes, apricots, etc., keeping the overall measurements the same.)
Store in an airtight container.
Good as either a snack or cereal.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel, core and slice pears into Fruit-Fresh mixed with water, or add Fruit-Fresh to sugar to prevent pears from turning dark. Drain well and layer 1 cup sugar to 1 quart pears, as you go.
Let set 2 to 4 hours.
There will be enough liquid to cook.
(Let set overnight to make pears tough, if desired.)
Cook until syrup is amber in color and thickens, about 2 1/2 hours.
Pears should be transparent and syrup should be thick, but not gummy when cooled. Test by dipping a little out and cool in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add diced onion and cook until tender. Add sauce, paste, juice and seasonings. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer about an hour or longer.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Dissolve each package of jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water and put in ice cube trays or aluminum pans to set.
Cube.
Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in cold water; add hot pineapple juice.
Cool until syrupy.
Add cream and jello cubes. Pour over crumbs and top with remaining cracker mixture.
Let set overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well with enough mayo to hold together.

title: salad dressing for macaroni or potato salad
directions: Pepper and celery seed as desired.

title: quick shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
In medium skillet, saute celery, green pepper and onion in reserved bacon drippings until crisp-tender.
Stir in bacon, cooked shrimp, chili powder, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and rice.
Heat thoroughly.

title: black bean and rice soup
directions: In a 12 inch skillet, cook sausage on medium heat until golden brown.
Place sausage on paper towel to drain.
Combine all ingredients except rice in a crock pot.
Cover; cook on low 8-10 hours.
Cook rice as directed.
Serve soup hot over cooked rice.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese and Ranch mix.
Put on tortillas and sprinkle other ingredients on.
Roll up and cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Chill and eat.

title: grits souffle
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in bowl and microwave stirring occasionally until liquid is absorbed.
Place margarine, cheese and grits into 1-quart souffle bowl or baking bowl, stirring until blended.
Allow to cool and add eggs and blend.
Place in 350° oven; bake 30 to 40 minutes to just light brown.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep in tightly covered bowl.
Use as needed.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pan half full.
Place in cold oven; turn oven to 400°.
Bake for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 25 muffins.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Take off stove and add oats, graham cracker crumbs, vanilla and coconut. To make chocolate, add 1 tablespoon cocoa.
Drop on wax paper to cool.
No cooking required.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cream butter in bowl.
Gradually blend in cream and cheese; stir until thoroughly mixed.
Set aside.
Cook fettuccini in boiling, salted water.
Drain and transfer to a warmed serving dish.
Pour the cheese mixture over the pasta and toss until pasta is well coated.
Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: honey whole-wheat bread
directions: In a small saucepan, heat milk until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add shortening, honey and salt, stirring until shortening is melted.
Let cool to lukewarm or tepid.
If possible, check temperature of warm water with thermometer.

title: marshmallow fugue bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, Add eggs and vanilla.
Add shifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350.
Remove-cover with small marshmallows. Return to oven until marshmallows are soft- about 5 minutes.
Cool and cut into 16 bars.

title: raspberry crunch
directions: In medium bowl, combine sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Add berries; toss to coat.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. In large bowl, combine oats, brown sugar and remaining 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon evenly over berries.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and topping is golden brown.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In shallow bowl, mix corn flake crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, garlic salt, basil, oregano and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then in crumb mixture, pressing lightly to coat.
Place, skin side up, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until coating is golden brown and chicken near bone is no longer pink.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine graham crackers, sugar and margarine.
Press in 9-inch pie tin.
Cook 6 minutes at 350° and cool.
Follow directions on Dream Whip package.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Put in cooled pie crust.
Drop cherry pie mix on top and chill.

title: hamburger oriental
directions: Cut onions into half rings.
Fry in bacon drippings.
Crumble up bouillon cubes and add these to the onions.
Quarter cabbage, then slice it sideways into onion-ring-width strips, no more than 1/2-inch wide.
Add to onion mixture.
Stir well so that all cabbage slices are coated with oil.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle salt over cabbage; reduce heat and cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir cabbage mixture from time to time.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix sugar and mayonnaise; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine rest of the ingredients.
Add sugar mixture.

title: bread sticks
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt and shortening. Add flour, kneading well.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Flatten out on a floured bread board; cut into strips about 1/2 x 4 inches. Twist a couple of times to form bread sticks.
Arrange on a cookie sheet to bake at 400° for 15 minutes; may be coated with egg-milk mixture, then sprinkled with poppy or sesame seed.

title: rita's french dressing
directions: Mix in a blender or electric beater.
Refrigerate in a covered jar or bottle.

title: pepper steak
directions: Broil meat until done.
Place in saucepan.
Season with garlic, salt and soy sauce.
Add 1/4 cup water; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add pepper, onion and celery; cook 10 minutes.
Mix flour with 1 cup water.
Add to saucepan, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: irish stew
directions: Cook (boil) meat and onions until tender.
Add potatoes and corn.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer on low 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly. Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to shortening mixture, mixing well. Blend in oats, Drop by tsp. onto greased cookie sheets. Bake in 350° oven 12-15 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Add egg, onion, mashed potatoes and peppers to salmon.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Shape into medium size patties.
Fry in oil until browned.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and margarine well.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Then add 1 cup flour at a time, beating well after each.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Bring to a boil the salad oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, catsup and lemon juice.
Pour over hot, drained macaroni.
Cool, then add salad dressing, tomatoes, onion, celery and pepper.

title: surprise chicken with a bone
directions: Put everything in the pot; then turn on the fire.
Make sure everything stays on the bottom.
Eat the food and drink the Coke.

title: "best in the west" bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In an ovenproof kettle, cook the beef, bacon and onion over moderate heat, stirring occasionally to break up any lumps, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until the beef is no longer pink and the bacon is slightly crisp.
Transfer the mixture to a sieve and let it drain.
Return the mixture to the kettle.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir until all is combined well. Bake the mixture, covered, in the middle of the oven for 1 hour. Serves about 20 as a side dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken for 35 minutes.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower until almost done; do not overcook.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-pinch pan. Spread broccoli and cauliflower in pan.
Tear chicken in small pieces; put over vegetables.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise together and spoon over chicken over vegetable mixture.
Cover entire casserole with cheese; break bread over casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until bread is brown and cheese melted.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: In Dutch oven, brown the sausage in the oil.
Remove both sausage and oil from the pot.
Return 2 tablespoons oil to pot. Add onions, celery, garlic and bell pepper.
Cover and stir frequently until brown.
Return sausage to mixture.
Add rice, water, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Mix well and simmer for 15 minutes using cover and stirring often.
Lower heat and steam 45 minutes stirring every 10 minutes or so to assure even cooking and prevent bottom from burning.

title: bob taylor's chili rellenos casserole
directions: Split chilies, discard seeds and veins and rinse in cold water.
Put a layer of opened chilies on the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Put Jack cheese on top of chilies.
Put another layer of the remaining chilies on top of the cheese.
Put the Cheddar cheese on the top of the second layer of chilies.

title: hungarian chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler, remove from boiling water, add sugar and water; blend.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add butter, one third at a time, beating thoroughly after each amount.
Makes enough frosting to cover a 9-inch layer cake or about 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: Peel and slice apple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in covered bowl.
Microwave on High for 11 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: grits and cheese
directions: Cook enough grits for one special little boy.
Stir in a little milk and butter and add lots of cheese.
Serve with love.

title: bacon omelet
directions: Fry bacon and pour off excess bacon drippings.
Combine mashed potatoes, milk, baking powder, seasonings and egg yolks; fold in egg whites.
Pour into skillet; sprinkle bacon over top.
Cook over low heat until puffed and brown.
Fold over; garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chitterlings
directions: Cook chitterlings slowly until almost tender.
Pour off most of liquid.
Add onion, garlic and salt and pepper to taste. Continue to cook until tender or can be cut with a fork.

title: icing for cake
directions: Cook a few minutes until icing turns light tan.
Do not overcook.
Then ice cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut 2 slices of bread and cover bottom of baking dish.
Mix chicken, onion, pepper, celery, mayonnaise, salt, pimiento and spread over bread.
Trim crust off 4 slices of bread and cover casserole.
Let set 1 hour or overnight.
Before baking, spoon on can of soup and bake 55 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle on cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift
together	all
the dry ingredients.
Beat the egg with the
milk
and
add it to the flour along with the melted butter. Stir
well.
Spread
the
batter in a buttered 9-inch pan and bake in a 375° preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until it is lightly browned.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Allow to cool, then add the orange juice.
Set in the refrigerator until it starts to congeal.
Add the cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Return to refrigerator to set.
This is especially good with turkey or wild fowl.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion with margarine until onions are soft.
Add Worcestershire sauce, sugar, tomatoes and tomato soup.
Salt to taste and sprinkle oregano.
Let simmer 1 to 3 hours.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix ziti and sauce in baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Blend in remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Heat until bubbly.
Add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice or can be combined with the noodles or rice and served in a baking dish.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add seasonings.
Put in casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Garnish with paprika. Serves 6 to 8.
Better if made the day before.

title: whole fried turkey
directions: Thaw turkey completely and wash thoroughly.
Freely season turkey skin and cavity with salt, red pepper and Season-All, rubbing seasoning in well.
Place cooking oil in a 20 to 26-quart pot or jambalaya pot, bringing oil to temperature hot enough to light match.
Place turkey in oil; reduce heat to slow boil.
Cook 45 minutes, turning every 8 to 10 minutes.
Make sure oil stays at a slow boil.
When golden brown, remove and cool.
Carves like a baked bird.
Delicious!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and chop it.
In a large heavy pan combine tomatoes and onion.
Cook until onion is done.
Add chicken and paprika; let it cook slowly to blend flavors.
Add Worcestershire sauce and soup.
Add cheese and mix well.
Add spaghetti.
Cook a short while on low heat.
Stir to keep from sticking.

title: nitey nites
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 30 minutes before starting.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then gradually add sugar; mixture will be stiff.
Add nuts, chips or whatever.
Fold into mixture.

title: chocolate chip ricotta cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add all other ingredients except chocolate chips.
Mix well, then stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together the coconut and nuts and put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Prepare the cake mix as directed and pour over the coconut and nut mixture.
Put margarine and cream cheese in a saucepan and heat enough to stir in the confectioners sugar.
Spoon over the cake mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely before cutting.
The longer it sits the moister it is.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute onions, celery and garlic in butter.
Add water, chicken broth and potatoes.
Cook until tender, then add the remaining ingredients.

title: prewash spray
directions: Put in spray bottle.
Spray spot or area.
Rub and toss in washer.
My mother-in-law, Genevieve Falk, gave me this recipe several years ago and it works.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix all and freeze.
Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving at room temperature.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale slowly just before serving.
Should be slushy.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Heat olive oil in pan over high heat.
Add garlic, onion and ham.
Cook until onion begins to wilt.
Add salt, sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Squeeze lemon into pan through napkin; shake out the seeds and add lemon halves.
Add vinegar. Bring to a boil and pour over the spinach; toss and cover the bowl with the inverted pan and allow spinach to wilt for approximately 1 minute.
Serve on warmed plates.
Garnish with lemon halves.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix
in
saucepan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Cook on medium heat until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat; cool
minute.
Add
vanilla,
salt, peanut butter and oatmeal. Stir mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: traditional fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan. Bring to a boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and immediately add marshmallows, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until blended and pour into pan to set.

title: butter icing
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, salt, milk and vanilla gradually beating until smooth and stiff enough to spread or use in pastry tube.

title: eight layer strawberry cake
directions: Bake cakes as directed.
Cut to make 8 layers.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.
Spread on each layer, topping with strawberries. Continue until all layers are complete.
Refrigerate.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil for about 1 minute.
Mix remainder of ingredients and pour over Special K.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna, melt cheese; add other ingredients.
Roll ball in walnuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: daddy's broiled shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp and wrap with bacon strips.
Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix together and pour over shrimp, then marinate for 15 to 30 minutes.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes, until done.
(Do not overcook, overcooking makes shrimp tough.)

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes; cover with water and boil 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain; let cool.
Combine 1/4 cup of butter, salt, pepper, onion, sour cream and soup.
Gently stir in potatoes and cheese. Spoon into lightly greased, large casserole dish.
Combine 3 tablespoons of butter and stuffing mix; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: beets with pineapple
directions: Cook juice drained from beets and pineapple in small saucepan with cornstarch, sugar and vinegar, stirring constantly until thickened. Add salt and pepper to taste, drained beets, pineapple and butter. Cook slowly for 20 minutes. Serve hot or cold. Makes 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Crumble cake when cooled and layer with other ingredients and Cool Whip.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; cool and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Mix dressing and flour; gradually stir in broth, Worcestershire sauce, browning agent/flavor enhancer and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture; simmer 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and mushrooms; cover.
Continue simmering 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and serve over.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour in buttered baking dish.

title: blueberry kramm
directions: Cook berries in water for 15 minutes.
Strain.
Add sugar and lemon juice to blueberry liquid.
Make a paste of the cornstarch and water.
Add to juices.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 to 4 minutes or until clear.
Pour into bowl to set.
Serve cold with heavy cream or whipped cream or stir 1 cup sour cream into mixture.

title: pasta romanoff
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse with hot water and drain.
In skillet, melt butter; add broccoli, onion and ham and cook 4 to 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Combine pasta and skillet mixture in serving bowl.
In same skillet, stir together sour cream, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over pasta mixture and mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: huckleberry pudding
directions: Bring
to
a
boil
the huckleberries, sugar and water. Mix dumplings
made
of
rest of the ingredients.
Spoon into warm fruit.
Cover and cook on slow heat for 5 minutes.	Leave covered; set off heat.
Serve warm, with cream or ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Separate chicken in bowl.
Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Blend in egg yolk. Fold in egg white. Arrange bread squares on cookie sheet.
Top each with a shrimp and cover with a rounded teaspoon of cheese mixture. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: parmesan cheese spread
directions: Blend all ingredients well and place in plastic container until serving time.
Spread on party rye bread, place under broiler until bubbly and warm.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse thin skinned potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes until brown and soft.

title: turkey divan
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions. Spread rice in bottom of a 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Cover with turkey, then broccoli in cheese sauce.
Mix together water chestnuts, soup, mushrooms and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Cover with onions and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, simmer 1 hour.
Remove onion and bay leaf before serving hot. Preparation time, 5 minutes.
Cooking time, 1 hour.

title: chili relleno bake
directions: Cook crumbled beef over medium heat until browned.
Add onion and garlic and cook until onion is limp.
Drain fat.
Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with half of the chilies; top with 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Add meat mixture and top with remaining chilies.
Beat together eggs and flour until smooth; add milk, salt and Tabasco. Blend well.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of cheese on top.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: egg and orange spinach
directions: Wash spinach in lukewarm water.
Drain well.
Chill thoroughly to crisp.
Peel and section oranges, reserving 1 to 2 tablespoons juice for dressing.
Combine reserved orange juice, salad oil, vinegar, sugar, sesame seed, celery salt and mustard, stirring until blended and sugar is dissolved.
Tear spinach into bite size pieces into large salad bowl.
Add orange sections and water chestnuts.
Toss to mix.
Add egg slices.
Pour dressing over all.
Toss gently to thoroughly mix and evenly coat ingredients.

title: macaroons
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown on edges.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix sugar, Bisquick, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with 1 slice of bacon.
Cover bottom of casserole with a layer of dried beef.
Place chicken on dried beef.
Cover all with mushroom soup mixed with the sour cream. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. (I bake for 2 hours.)

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream butter; add other ingredients and mix by hand.
Shape into one inch balls.
Chill or freeze.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 30 balls.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, milk, flour and baking powder.
Melt butter in cooking pan.
