Add mixture and fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake in medium oven until brown.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean broccoli, cauliflower and celery.
Cut into bite-size pieces into bowl.
Add onions, bacon and carrots.

title: better than potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, radishes, eggs, cucumber, celery and onion. Combine mayonnaise or Miracle Whip, mustard and salt. Mix well. Pour over rice mixture and toss. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serves 12 to 14.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Flatten chicken breasts; lay out ham on top of chicken breasts and season each with salt, pepper and thyme.
Roll up each filled breast; roll in melted butter and corn flakes.
Fasten each with toothpicks; place in sprayed shallow baking dish.
Place in preheated 350° oven; bake 35 minutes.
In a saucepan, combine soup, sour cream, lemon juice, seasoning and any leftover cheese slices (broken up).
Bring mixture to a light simmer until cheese melts.
Remove chicken from oven and pour sauce over all; return to oven for 10 minutes of baking.

title: lisa's lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger meat; add chopped onion and garlic salt.
Drain hamburger meat and add Sloppy Joes mix and tomatoes; mix well. Cook lasagne noodles as directed on package.
Butter large baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Alternately layer in dish the noodles, meat, olives and cheese.
Top with cheese and olives.
Bake at 425° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked flounder fillets
directions: Wash
and
pat	dry
flounder
fillets	and
arrange in aluminum foil baking dish, skin side down.	Sprinkle basil and pepper over fillets, then
add
lemon
juice,
soda and garlic powder.
Cut butter or margarine into several pieces and place on top of the fillets until
all
used.
Bake	at 375° for 1/2 hour or until fillets
are tender.
Serve with baked potatoes. Serves 2.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, pineapple and milk in saucepan.
Cook, stirring frequently, to soft ball stage, 236°.
Let cool slightly. Add vanilla.
Beat until thick and smooth.
Pour into greased pan. Cut into squares when hard.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together.
Add shortening or oil and vanilla and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirty rice with shrimp
directions: Heat cooking oil; stir in flour until golden brown.
Add onion, garlic and shrimp.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups water and 1 cup raw rice.
Cook on medium heat until water is almost gone.
Cover and simmer on lowest heat for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan evenly on bottom and up sides of pie pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: honey cake(israel)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat bottom and sides of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan with 1 teaspoon oil.
Sprinkle the pan with 2 tablespoons flour, tipping from side to side.
Cover evenly.
Turn pan upside down and rap sharply to remove excess flour.
Stir raisins and orange peel in a bowl with 2 tablespoons flour until evenly and lightly coated.
Set aside.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a hard boil, then drop in Hi Ho crackers and let boil 2 minutes, without stirring, but be sure all crackers are covered with mixture.
Pour in pie crust and top with cinnamon and cut up butter.
Put on top crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until golden brown.

title: spiced hot drink(finjan qirfeh)
directions: Boil spices in water until it is dark colored.
Put 1 teaspoon sugar and one nut in each cup.
Serves 4.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons of sugar, and melted butter. Mix well and pat onto the bottom of a 9-inch spring form pan.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with flour-sugar mixture.
Cover with grated cheese and then crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brandy slush
directions: Stir water and sugar over heat until sugar dissolves.
Set aside to cool.
Steep tea bags in boiling water for 20 minutes. Set aside to cool.
Combine orange juice, lemonade, brandy, tea and sugar water.
Put in container and freeze.
Stir occasionally until frozen.
Serve a couple of scoops with 50/50 poured over in a glass.

title: easy-do fudge
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk in large heavy saucepan. Over low heat, bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes, stirring to avoid scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously, making certain particles are dissolved.

title: sauerkraut noodle casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Cook noodles in salted water; drain.
Mix sugar and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl (makes 2-quart size or one large casserole).
Sprinkle with pepper and grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Seed peppers.
Chop or put in food processor.
Mix peppers with sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute; lower fire and cook 5 minutes, then add liquid pectin.
Pour into warmed clean jelly jars or mold.
Make sure jelly lids seal.

title: pesto
directions: In the bowl of food processor or in blender container, place all ingredients.
Process in a pulsating motion, turning machine on and off until blended.

title: swedish orange cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add orange rind and juice, mix well.
Add sifted flour a little at a time until mixture is firm.
Shape into a roll.
Chill 1 hour.
When ready to bake, slice thin.
Brush tops with unbeaten egg white and sprinkle with broken nuts and sugar.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 2 loaves.

title: quick rice and kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1-inch slices.
Prepare rice according to directions, adding kielbasa to water before rice.
Garnish with parsley or scallions.
Easy and delicious!

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and egg whites in a large mixing bowl. Add oil, honey, molasses and vanilla.
Sift flour with dry ingredients. Add wheat germ and flour mixture to eggs.
Stir well.
Add drained pineapple, carrots, raisins and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack. Frost with Lemon Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Place peppers, sugar and vinegar in a large saucepan; bring to a rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Add the Certo; bring to a boil again and boil for 1 minute.
Pour into sterile jelly glasses and seal.
Serve as an appetizer atop cream cheese; spread on Triscuits.
Makes 7 to 8 jelly glasses.

title: tamale pie
directions: Spread nacho chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put tamales on chips and cover with browned ground beef.
Pour chili on top and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix margarine, syrup and sugar. Bring to boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add cream of tartar, salt and soda. Stir until foamy.
Pour over popped corn. Spread on cookie sheet after mixing.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour. Parched peanuts may be added, if desired.

title: chocolate whipped cream
directions: Combine well, but not whipping.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Then whip.
Will generously frost an angel food cake.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Blend together the first 3 ingredients and press on the bottom of a cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Brown and saute beef and onion.
Mix all soups, then add beef mixture and cheeses.
Layer the tortillas with the mixture and the beef; sprinkle top layer with cheese.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put a layer of crackers in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Drain asparagus; save juice.
Spread one can asparagus spears on the layer of crackers.
Spread 1/2 pound of the grated cheese over the asparagus.
Dilute soup with 1/2 can of water and/or juice from the asparagus.
Pour 1 cup of diluted soup over cheese.
Repeat directions to make a second layer of ingredients.
Crush or crumble enough Ritz crackers to make a layer covering the mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk in a shallow bowl; set aside.
On waxed paper, lightly coat chicken with flour, then dip in soup mix.
Then coat with stuffing mix.

title: my peach cobbler
directions: Drain the peaches.
Pour the peaches in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pour the cake mix, right from the box, over the peaches, taking out any lumps in the mix.
Cut the margarine in small slices or melt it; spread or pour the margarine over the the top of the spice cake.
Make sure all is covered with margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
The crust should be a little crusty.
This serves 6 to 8.

title: spicy tomato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a salad bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
Then mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over top of salad.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: vegetable salad with feta cheese(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Rub interior of large wooden salad bowl with cut side of garlic.
Add and toss remaining ingredients.

title: one pot meal
directions: Cut cabbage as for stir-fry; place in Dutch oven pot.
Cut potatoes in chunks; place on top of cabbage.
Salt cabbage and potatoes.
Cut sausages into 2-inch pieces; place on top of potatoes.
Cut apples in wedges; place on top of sausages. Sprinkle sugar on apples.
Add water; simmer until all vegetables are done (about 45 minutes).
Serve with cornbread.
Serves 8.

title: kalops
directions: Coat meat with flour and brown in hot oil in Dutch oven. Remove meat.
Stir in 2 cups water and cook and stir to loosen brown bits.
Add meat and remaining ingredients.
Cook and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add more water during cooking time as needed.
Remove allspice and bay leaves.
Serve with pickled beets and mashed potatoes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine sauce mix, paste, sauce and water in medium saucepan. Bring to boil over low heat. Remove from heat. Combine Ricotta, salt, spinach, 1/4 cup Parmesan and egg; set aside. Spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Place 1/2 noodles over sauce and spread with 1/2 spinach mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/2 sauce. Repeat. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix cake as box directs; omit oil and use Miracle Whip.
Bake as directed on box.

title: bar cheese spread
directions: Mix well in blender or with mixer.
This recipe tastes similar to Winschuler's bar cheese.

title: low-fat strawberry truffle
directions: Tear cake in small pieces and layer half in glass bowl. Prepare pudding according to box and fold Cool Whip into pudding. Layer half of mixture over cake.
Spoon half of strawberries over pudding.
Repeat layers.
Chill and enjoy.

title: three cheese tuna casserole
directions: Cook pasta.
Heat soup, milk and cheeses together.
Stir until cheeses are melted.
Combine pasta, sauce, peas and carrots, French fried onions and tuna together.

title: german onion bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar, onions and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed or 300 strokes by hand.
Scrape sides of bowl often.
Add remaining flour; blend with spoon until smooth, scraping batter from sides of bowl.
Cover with cloth; let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 30 minutes).
Stir down batter by beating about 25 strokes.
Spread evenly into greased loaf pan.
Batter will be sticky; flour hands and pat top and sides to smooth.
Let rise again to double in bulk, about 45 minutes.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in a 375° oven.
Remove from pan at once.
Cool away from draft.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss first five ingredients together in a bowl.
Best if left in refrigerator overnight.
Mix last five ingredients.
Add to chicken mixture.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: di's chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken 1 hour.
Cool and dice.
Combine with celery, mayonnaise and pineapple.
Before serving, add almonds and chow mein noodles.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread pie filling evenly on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Layer undrained pineapple on top of cherries. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple. Cover with melted margarine. Top with coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Simmer apples and juice for 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch; simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until thickened.
Stir in cinnamon.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; dot with butter.
Cover top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In a 2-quart pan, saute onion and herbs in olive oil until tender.
Add potatoes, broth and water.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: autumn soup
directions: Boil water, add broken up meat, onion and celery.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add onion soup mix and orzo; cook 15 minutes more.
Add Veg-All, including liquid, Campbell's soup and tomatoes, crushed. Cook until vegetables are soft and orzo is cooked.

title: finger salad
directions: Mix vegetables together in large bowl and toss with marinade for 24 hours.

title: spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
Add garlic and chopped onion. Brown.
Add 1 can tomato soup plus 2 cans water.
Bring to a boil, at least 10 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti and stir or pour over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Thaw juices and strawberries. Drain cherries and chop.
Slice bananas.
Mix all ingredients and freeze in individual cupcake liners.
After frozen, store in plastic bags.
To serve, thaw slightly before serving.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: cabbage salad (kapusta)
directions: Shred cabbage, then heat all other ingredients together to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage and stir.
Cool.
Refrigerate in a sealed bowl.
Stir several times a day.
Make 3 to 4 days ahead for best flavor.

title: tex mex soup
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Chop nuts. Set aside. Beat eggs and gradually beat in sugar, then vegetable oil. Combine dry ingredients. Add to first mixture alternately with zucchini. Stir in raisins and chopped nuts. Add vanilla. Divide batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 55 minutes in 350° oven. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on wire racks. Freezes well.

title: italian green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in crock pot.
Cook on low heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased souffl dish or 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm in center.

title: dumplings and cabbage
directions: If you do not have large potatoes, use more of smaller ones. Cut potatoes in half; scoop out the middle, leaving 1/4 inch of potato on the skin.
I use a grapefruit spoon, and it works like a charm.
Brush the inside and the skin with oil.
Place potatoes in a baking pan, skin side up.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes, until crisp. Turn over and broil 10 to 15 minutes more, until brown on the edges.

title: mandarin orange jello mold
directions: Mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set.
Mix instant lemon pudding with 1 1/3 cups milk.
Mix with 1 package of Cool Whip.
Put on top of Jell-O, which is firm.
Let set overnight. May be cut in squares or spooned out.

title: connie's green beans
directions: Cook all together.
Good with Steak Royale recipe.
If leftovers, combine for stew.

title: jack's biscuits
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Gradually add milk. Roll about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with round cookie cutter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 11 to 12 biscuits.

title: beef vegetable borsch
directions: In large kettle, melt butter.
Saute vegetables for 3 minutes. Add tomatoes, broth, vinegar, beets and meat; bring to boil. Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Season to taste.
Top with sour cream.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth and milk.
Heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in chicken and veggies.
Put in shell. Cook, uncovered, at 425° until brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: prize custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Combine scalded milk, sugar and salt. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Gradually add milk mixture to slightly beaten eggs, stirring until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top generously with nutmeg.
Bake on center shelf of oven, which has been preheated to 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and continue to bake 10 to 20 minutes or until done.
(Filling should feel fairly firm to a light touch of the fingertip.
Don't overbake.)
Cool to room temperature and serve.
High beginning temperature and glass pie plate will eliminate soggy, underdone crust.

title: date bread loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, dissolve soda in water and pour over dates.

title: pumpkin harvest bars
directions: Combine raisins, walnuts and 2 tablespoons flour.
Sift together 1/2 cup flour, salt, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Set aside.
Melt shortening in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Remove from heat.
Blend in pumpkin, vanilla and eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add to dry mixture.
Pour in a well greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Mix carrots, bell pepper, onion and celery.
Mix tomato soup, vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, pepper, woo and mustard.
Pour over first 4 ingredients. Marinate overnight.

title: aunt mattie's fluffy waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Add butter. Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in waffle iron until waffle stops steaming.

title: virginia's potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except topping) together.
Put in large casserole dish.

title: tasty relish
directions: Chop green tomatoes and peppers.
Add salt and let drain overnight.
Peel and chop ripe tomatoes and onions.
Combine all ingredients in heavy large pot.
Simmer about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal at once.
Makes about 4 to 6 pints.

title: apricot slices
directions: Mix flour and salt; rub in fats and stir in sugar.
Mix to a stiff paste with beaten egg and a little milk, if necessary.
Cut pastry in two; roll out thinly both same size.
Place one piece on greased baking sheet; cover with jam.
Moisten edges of pastry. Cover with other pieces and nip together.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 20 minutes.
Cool; cut into slices and dredge with confectioners sugar.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter
in hot milk, pour over 1 cup bread crumbs, mix well
and
add to cooked, blended squash.
Add seasonings. Beat eggs
well
and add to mixture.
Pour into buttered dish. Top with 1/2
cup buttered bread crumbs and bake at 300° until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Cook bacon slightly, but not crisp.
Cook a piece of bacon for each piece of chicken.
Line lightly greased casserole with chipped or dried beef.
Wrap each piece of chicken with bacon strip and place on dried beef.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken and cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours. Uncover last half hour to brown chicken.

title: cheese pepper bread
directions: Grease two 1 pound coffee cans.
In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add 1 1/3 cups of flour, sugar, salt, soda, sour cream and egg.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Stir in remaining flour, cheese and pepper.
Divide batter between cans. Let rise in warm place 50 minutes.
(Batter will rise slightly; will not double.) Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cans immediately.
Cool slightly before slicing.

title: vanilla-raspberry trifle
directions: Prepare pudding mix as label directs.
Cool slightly.
Stir in 2 teaspoons vanilla extract.
Place plastic wrap on surface of pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Grease pan (I spray with Pam) and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Sprinkle chopped pecans in bottom of pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Mix for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Add icing to batter; mix well and pour into pan on top of pecans. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until brown.
(I use the toothpick test.)
Tube pan, Bundt pan or sheet cake pan may be used.
This cake is so good and so easy.
Enjoy.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a glass bowl, combine oil and onions.
Cook on High for 7 minutes, until onions are tender.
Stir in celery and green pepper. Cover; cook on High for 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first nine ingredients and shape into balls the size you prefer.
Pour oil in large skillet, add meat balls and brown. Remove meat balls and drain on paper towels.
Pour off oil. Heat chili sauce and grape jelly in same skillet until melted.
Add meat balls and stir until coated.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: date nut coconut cookies
directions: In large pan, melt butter.
Add eggs, sugar and dates.
Cook 5 minutes until dates are melted.
Mixture will be dark brown. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, Rice Krispies and walnuts. Roll into small balls; roll in coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: burgundy beef stew(low calorie)
directions: Trim fat from steak and cut steak into 1-inch pieces.
Add steak to spray coated pan and cook until browned.
In a Dutch oven, add cooking spray, steak, thyme and garlic; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in wine, tomato paste and bay leaves; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until steak is tender.
Add beef broth, 1/2 cup water and next 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water; stir well. Add to stew and stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper. Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple and the juice to a boil.
Add Jell-O and let set.
Put into a mixing bowl and beat in the yogurt and Cool Whip; blend them together with the Jell-O mixture.
Pour into your serving bowl and let chill for 2 hours or more.

title: steak pizziola
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil in a large frying pan until golden. Add crushed tomatoes, parsley, oregano, basil and salt.
Trim excess fat from steak; wash and pat dry.
Put steak in sauce. Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add 1 cup of water and continue to simmer for another 15 minutes.
Boil water for pasta in a 3-quart pot according to package directions.
Take steak out of sauce and cut into serving pieces.
Add sauce to pasta and serve with grated cheese.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Salt and
pepper chicken and place in a casserole dish. Mix sour
cream
and
mushroom	soup
together	and
pour over chicken.
Bake
covered,
for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring once every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Store in a tightly closed jar.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine dry cake mix and oats in a large bowl and add butter. Stir until crumbly.
Measure half of crumb mixture (about 3 cups) into pan. Press firmly to cover bottom.
Combine preserves and water. Stir until blended.
Spread preserves over crumb mixture, then sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over preserves and pat firmly to make top even.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 23 minutes or until top is very light brown.
Cool in pan on rack, then cut into bars.
Store in an airtight container.

title: green chili chicken
directions: Boil chicken with onion and seasonings until tender.
Cool until easy to handle.
Remove bones from chicken and put pieces in a large, buttered casserole.
Layer top of chicken with torn pieces of tortillas.
Next, layer with green chilies, mixed with sour cream.
Repeat layer of tortilla pieces, topped with Cheddar cheese, using a generous amount of cheese.
Place another layer of tortilla pieces over cheese and top with a layer of Jack cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until heated through and cheeses are all melted.

title: spaghetti special
directions: Combine cooked spaghetti, eggs, Parmesan cheese and parsley. Butter a large (9 x 13-inch) baking dish.
Layer half of the spaghetti and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and spoon Meat Sauce over it.
Can be made ahead, refrigerated and cooked when needed.
Serve with Meat Sauce.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: graham cracker chocolate chip square
directions: Mix first two ingredients together and use a little bit of cold water to rinse can.
Add semi-sweet chocolate bits and mix all together.
Put in 8 x 8 x 2 inch greased pan.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix thoroughly and roll in crushed pecans.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Mix together onion soup, chili sauce and Coke.
Place in baking pan.
Pour soup mixture over brisket.
Cover and bake 4 to 5 hours.
Remove meat and slice.
Return to sauce.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Flour pork roast.
Salt and pepper it.
Add enough water to almost cover.
Pour the following mixture on top: vinegar, chili sauce, onions, sugar, garlic and red pepper.
Cook on top of stove and keep turning.
Cook at least 4 to 5 hours or until meat cooks down and falls apart.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, mix all ingredients together, except milk, flour and mayonnaise.
In a small bowl, mix together milk, flour and mayonnaise.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: reubens
directions: Put dressing on both sides of bread.
Add sauerkraut, corned beef, mustard and slices of cheese.
Put under broiler and toast until brown.

title: holiday rice dressing
directions: Cook rice
and
set
aside.
Cook and drain ground beef and sausage.
Combine
onion, garlic, bell pepper and water in large skillet.
Cook
until
tender.
Add
cooked meat.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour
with 1 tablespoon oil; add to meat mixture. Mix together
hard-boiled eggs, Worcestershire sauce, Kitchen Bouquet, dash
of
Tabasco,
salt and pepper to taste, chicken broth,
chopped
parsley, green onions, mushrooms and almonds. Simmer until done.

title: pork chops with amber rice
directions: Brown chops in heavy skillet; season with salt and pepper. Place rice in 12 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish and pour orange juice over rice.
Arrange chops on rice.
Pour chicken soup over all. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown bread
directions: Cut up dates.
Sprinkle soda over dates.
Add boiling water. Let stand and cool some.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Add date mixture and mix well.
Fill cans half full and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Do not grease cans.
Batter will not stick.
Wrap in foil while very hot.
This makes 6 cans.
(Use any tin can, such as a green bean or corn can.)

title: chicken in lemon sauce
directions: Cook chicken in butter until brown and tender.
Place chicken in ovenproof serving dish.
Cook and stir wine, lemon peel and lemon juice over medium heat for 1 minute.
Stir in salt and white pepper.
Gradually pour in cream, stirring constantly until hot; do not boil.
Pour cream sauce over chicken; sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms.
Broil chicken about 6 inches from heat source until lightly browned.

title: maui slush
directions: Mix together in ice cream pail.
Freeze overnight.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Spray or butter a 2-quart casserole; spread bottom with 1 cup Stove Top stuffing.
Parboil zucchini, carrot and onion to tender-crisp.
Drain and pour over stuffing in dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup stuffing over zucchini mixture.
Spread soup over, then melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and somewhat brown.

title: toasted oatmeal cookies
directions: In medium skillet over medium heat saute oats in butter until light brown.
Remove from heat and cool.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; stir well.
Add oats, raisins and walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Enjoy.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° until brown and crisp.

title: baked stuffed chicken fillets
directions: Combine spinach, cheeses and onions in a bowl. Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper. Spoon 1/4 of spinach mixture into one fillet.
Roll fillet around spinach.
Wrap strip of bacon around each fillet.
Place in lightly greased baking dish.
Repeat for remaining fillets. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until done. Serves 4.

title: white cake
directions: Mix liquid ingredients and sugar.
Set aside.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Do not overstir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together.
Best if it sets 1 or 2 days before eating.

title: banquet sweet rolls
directions: Put
the
yeast
in a bowl.
Add the 1 tablespoon sugar and work in stirred together and melted butter and milk.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Knead together until smooth.
Put in buttered bowl.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.

title: big red ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thickened.
Add cream, vanilla and salt; mix thoroughly.
Pour into freezer can.
Add Big Red to fill line on can and stir well.
Freeze as directed.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Combine water, spaghetti sauce, ground beef and tomato sauce in a bowl.
Cover bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Arrange layer of uncooked noodles, slightly overlapping on top of sauce.
Spread half the Ricotta and half the Mozzarella over noodles.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Add another layer of sauce.
Repeat noodles and cheeses.
Top with noodles.
Pour on remaining sauce and spread to edge.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty foil and set on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife goes easily through pasta.
Let stand covered on rack for 10 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Combine ingredients in skillet and cook, stirring occasionally to combine flavors.
Simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.
Serve over 1 pound cooked pasta or 4 cups cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp curry casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute mushrooms, onions and green pepper in butter.
Add cooked rice and other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole topped with cracker crumbs and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave barbecue
directions: Combine
beef
and onions in casserole.
Cover.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on	High.
Add
catsup,
vinegar, sugar, salt and mustard. Microwave 5
minutes
on High until bubbly, stirring after 4 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns or as desired.

title: onion cake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Discard pan drippings.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Cool.
Combine sour cream, flour and salt; add beaten eggs.
Stir in bacon and onions; set aside. Separate rolls into 4 triangles.
Pat dough into bottom and 1-inch up sides of a greased 9-inch square pan.
Pinch sides together to seal.
Pour onion mixture over dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top is set and crust is golden.
Cool slightly before cutting.
Cut into small squares.
Serve warm.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add rice; remove from heat.
Put 1/2 of chopped cabbage into baking dish.
Add one layer of hamburger and rice.
Add rest of cabbage and hamburger and stir. Then mix salt, pepper, tomato sauce, tomato soup and water.
Pour over cabbage and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
When done, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add soups and tomatoes.
Put layer of crushed Doritos, layer of soup mixture, then layer of chicken in casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Top with 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.

title: go to bed cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add sugar gradually.
Beat until very stiff.
Add salt, food coloring and flavoring.
Drop on greased pan from a teaspoon.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place sheet in oven.
Turn off oven and leave in overnight.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Place chickens in a large pot and cover with water.
Simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken and reserve broth.
Skin and bone chicken; set aside.

title: tandori chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Add all ingredients.
Marinate for 4 hours, then bake for 40 minutes.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Slice and toss the first 5 ingredients.
Serve with Avocado Dressing made with avocado and salsa blended together.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pie filling, beaten eggs and extract together. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
While still warm, cover with icing.

title: rouladen
directions: Slice beef roast with electric knife and pound each slice with a meat mallet to tenderize and flatten each slice out.
Spread mustard over meat slice.
Sprinkle with onion powder and top with one or two bacon strips.
Roll the meat and secure with toothpicks. Repeat with each meat slice.
Brown rolled meat slice in frying pan.
Place browned meat rolls in large pot with beef oxo cubes or powder and water to cover.
Let simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Remove meat rolls to platter and thicken gravy with flour. Then move meat rolls back to thickened gravy and simmer for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Add Soda to sifted Flour and sift again.
Cream the Butter with Sugar with 6 Egg Yolks in a large mixing bowl.
Beat Well. Gradually add Sour Cream and flour mixture; starting and ending with the flour.
Beat Egg Whites until they hold peaks.
Gently fold into the mixture.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans at 325 for 1-1/4 hours or until a toothpick comes out fairly dry.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Put in 1-quart loaf pan. Bake 1 hour.

title: cheese hermits
directions: Mix and form into small balls. Bake 45 minutes

title: peach marshmallow pie
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and press in bottom and sides of pie tin.
Chill until needed.
Cook and stir marshmallows and milk in double boiler until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice mixed with water.
Cool.
Fold in marshmallow mixture and cream.
Put in layers with fresh peaches.
Chill until firm.

title: bessie's dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients with enough water to roll out.
Let set for 30 minutes before cutting them.
After broth comes to boil, put in dumplings.
Put lid on and simmer until dumplings are tender.

title: mexican casserole
directions: *For easy dividing, crush each bag separately.

title: easy mashed potato leftovers
directions: Saute ham and onions with butter until tender.
Add mashed potatoes and mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dip approximately 1/2 cup potatoes in pyrex dish until all are in dish. Shred mozzarella cheese and place on top of potatoes.
Place in oven until warm and cheese has melted about 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; place in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes and onions; pour mushroom soup all on top of pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine 4 1/2 cups flour, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine eggs, milk and yeast mixture; add to flour mixture, stirring well (dough will be sticky).
Cover dough and refrigerate overnight.

title: snackeroons
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork in a large mixing bowl until a dough forms.
Drop by level teaspoons onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes. Remove to cool.
Serve warm or cold.

title: oat and raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In a different bowl, blend milk, molasses, Egg Beaters and Butter Buds.
Add liquid ingredients with dry ingredients until moistened.
Spray nonfat cooking spray on muffin papers in pan.
Fill each cup 3/4 full. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Yields 24 to 28 muffins.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges; add enough water with juice to make 3 cups.
Dissolve pudding and jello mixes in this liquid and cook until thickens.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Add sliced onion, crisp and crumbled bacon and raisins.

title: "blondies" by twana mccleary
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Beat in a bowl at medium speed the butter and sugar for 2 minutes. Beat in egg and vanilla.
In a small bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt; stir into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack before cutting.
Makes 12 brownies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine 1 cup Monterey Jack, 1 cup Cheddar, cream cheese, 1/4 cup picante sauce, chicken, red pepper, green onions and cumin. Spoon equally in center of each tortilla.
Roll and place, seam side down, in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon remaining picante sauce over tortillas.
Cover with remaining cheese.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: mable e. fowlkes' coconut cream candy
directions: Boil sugar, salt and milk together, stirring just until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to soft ball stage (test by dropping a small amount in cold water).
Add coconut, vanilla and cream by beating with a wooden spoon until mixture becomes creamy.
Turn into a buttered pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, place stick of margarine on top. Microwave two minutes or until margarine is melted, stir immediately. Add milk and stir again, stir in vanilla. Turn into a pie dish and refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Add cracker crumbs to absorb moisture so that meat can be formed into balls.
Brown meat balls in hot oil about 5 to 7 minutes.
Put meat balls into sauce and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: bread pudding with raisins
directions: Combine the milk,
eggs, honey, sugar and flavor;
beat well. In a greased baking pan, put the bread.
Pour the other ingredients.
Bake in a
moderate
oven
at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife is
inserted
in the center and comes out clean. Before baking, sprinkle
the
top
of
the
pudding
with
the nutmeg.
Serves 6 to 8.
